  <char style="fqa">I will place help upon a warrior </char>. Some translate the word for
  <char style="fqa">help </char>as
  <char style="fqa">crown </char>and that is how the ULT has translated the word here.
</note></para>
<para style="q1">I have raised up one chosen from among the people.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="20" style="v" />I have chosen David my servant;</para>
<para style="q1">with my holy oil have I anointed him.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="21" style="v" />My hand will support him;</para>
<para style="q1">my arm will strengthen him.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="22" style="v" />No enemy will deceive him;</para>
<para style="q1">no son of wickedness will oppress him.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="23" style="v" />I will crush his enemies before him;</para>
<para style="q1">I will kill those who hate him.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="24" style="v" />My truth and my covenant faithfulness will be with him;</para>
<para style="q1">by my name he will be victorious.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="25" style="v" />I will place his hand over the sea</para>
<para style="q1">and his right hand over the rivers.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="26" style="v" />He will call out to me, 'You are my Father,</para>
<para style="q1">my God, and the rock of my salvation.'
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="27" style="v" />I also will place him as my firstborn son,</para>
<para style="q1">the most exalted of the kings of the earth.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="28" style="v" />I will extend my covenant faithfulness to him forever;</para>
<para style="q1">and my covenant with him will be secure.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="29" style="v" />I will make his descendants endure forever</para>
<para style="q1">and his throne as enduring as the skies above.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="30" style="v" />If his children forsake my law</para>
<para style="q1">and do not walk in my regulations,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="31" style="v" />if they break my rules</para>
<para style="q1">and do not keep my commands,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="32" style="v" />then will I punish their rebellion with a rod</para>
<para style="q1">and their iniquity with blows.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="33" style="v" />But I will not remove my steadfast love from him</para>
<para style="q1">or be unfaithful to my promise.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="34" style="v" />I will not break my covenant</para>
<para style="q1">or change the words of my lips.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="35" style="v" />Once and for all I have sworn by my holiness—</para>
<para style="q1">I will not lie to David:</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="36" style="v" />his descendants will continue forever</para>
<para style="q1">and his throne as long as the sun before me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="37" style="v" />It will be established forever like the moon,</para>
<para style="q1">the faithful witness in the sky."
<char style="qs">Selah</char>
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="38" style="v" />But you have refused and rejected;</para>
<para style="q1">you have been angry with your anointed king.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="39" style="v" />You have renounced the covenant of your servant.</para>
<para style="q1">You have desecrated his crown on the ground.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="40" style="v" />You have broken down all his walls.</para>
<para style="q1">You have ruined his strongholds.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="41" style="v" />All who pass by have robbed him.</para>
<para style="q1">He has become an object of disgust to his neighbors.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="42" style="v" />You have raised the right hand of his enemies;</para>
<para style="q1">you have made all his enemies rejoice.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="43" style="v" />You turn back the edge of his sword</para>
<para style="q1">and have not made him stand when in battle.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="44" style="v" />You have brought his splendor to an end;</para>
<para style="q1">you have brought down his throne to the ground.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="45" style="v" />You have shortened the days of his youth.</para>
