<chapter number="90" style="c" />
<para style="d">A prayer of Moses the man of God.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Lord, you have been our refuge</para>
<para style="q1">throughout all generations.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Before the mountains were formed,</para>
<para style="q1">or you formed the earth and the world,</para>
<para style="q1">from everlasting to everlasting, you are God.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />You return man to dust,</para>
<para style="q1">and you say, "Return, you descendants of mankind."</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />For a thousand years in your sight</para>
<para style="q1">are as yesterday when it is past,</para>
<para style="q1">and as a watch in the night.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />You sweep them away as with a flood and they sleep;</para>
<para style="q1">in the morning they are like the grass that sprouts up.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />In the morning it blooms and grows up;</para>
<para style="q1">in the evening it withers and dries up.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Truly, we are consumed in your anger,</para>
<para style="q1">and in your wrath we are terrified.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />You have set our iniquities before you,</para>
<para style="q1">our hidden sins in the light of your presence.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />Our life passes away under your wrath;</para>
<para style="q1">our years quickly pass like a sigh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />Our years are seventy,</para>
<para style="q1">or even eighty if we are healthy;</para>
<para style="q1">but even our best years are marked by trouble and sorrow.</para>
<para style="q1">Yes, they pass quickly, and we fly away.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />Who knows the intensity of your anger,</para>
<para style="q1">and your wrath that is equal to the fear of you?</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />So teach us to consider our life</para>
