<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="22" style="v" />But Yahweh has been my high tower,</para>
<para style="q1">and my God has been the rock of my refuge.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="23" style="v" />He will bring on them their own iniquity</para>
<para style="q1">and will cut them off in their own wickedness.</para>
<para style="q1">Yahweh our God will cut them off.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="95" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Oh come, let us sing to Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">let us sing joyfully to the rock of our salvation.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Let us enter his presence with thanksgiving;</para>
<para style="q1">let us sing to him with psalms of praise.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />For Yahweh is a great God</para>
<para style="q1">and a great King superior to all gods.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />In his hand are the depths of the earth;</para>
<para style="q1">the heights of the mountains are his.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />The sea is his, for he made it,</para>
<para style="q1">and his hands formed the dry land.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Oh come, let us worship and bow down;</para>
<para style="q1">let us kneel before Yahweh, our Creator:</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />For he is our God,</para>
<para style="q1">and we are the people of his pasture and the sheep of his hand.</para>
<para style="q1">Today—oh, that you would hear his voice!
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />"Do not harden your heart, as at Meribah,</para>
<para style="q1">or as on the day of Massah in the wilderness,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />where your forefathers tested me</para>
<para style="q1">and tried me, though they had seen my deeds.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />For forty years I was angry with that generation</para>
<para style="q1">and said, 'This is a people whose hearts wander astray;</para>
<para style="q1">they have not known my ways.'</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />Therefore I vowed in my anger</para>
<para style="q1">that they would never enter into my resting place."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="96" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Oh, sing to Yahweh a new song;</para>
<para style="q1">sing to Yahweh, all the earth.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Sing to Yahweh, bless his name;</para>
<para style="q1">announce his salvation day after day.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Declare his glory among the nations,</para>
<para style="q1">his marvelous deeds among all the nations.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />For Yahweh is great and is to be praised greatly.</para>
<para style="q1">He is to be feared above all other gods.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />For all the gods of the nations are idols,</para>
<para style="q1">but it is Yahweh who made the heavens.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Splendor and majesty are in his presence.</para>
<para style="q1">Strength and beauty are in his sanctuary.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Ascribe to Yahweh, you clans of peoples,</para>
<para style="q1">ascribe praise to Yahweh for his glory and strength.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Give to Yahweh the glory that his name deserves.</para>
<para style="q1">Bring an offering and come into his courts.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />Bow down to Yahweh in the splendor of holiness;</para>
<para style="q1">tremble before him, all the earth.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />Say among the nations, "Yahweh reigns."</para>
<para style="q1">The world also is established; it cannot be shaken.</para>
<para style="q1">He judges the peoples fairly.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />Let the heavens be glad, and let the earth rejoice;</para>
<para style="q1">let the sea roar and that which fills it shout with joy.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />Let the fields rejoice and all that is in them.</para>
<para style="q1">Then let all the trees in the forest shout for joy</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />before Yahweh, for he is coming.</para>
<para style="q1">He is coming to judge the earth.</para>
<para style="q1">He will judge the world with righteousness</para>
<para style="q1">and the peoples with his faithfulness.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="97" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Yahweh reigns; let the earth rejoice;</para>
<para style="q1">let the many coastlands be glad.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Clouds and darkness surround him.</para>
<para style="q1">Righteousness and justice are the foundation of his throne.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Fire goes before him</para>
<para style="q1">and consumes his adversaries on every side.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />His lightning lights up the world;</para>
<para style="q1">the earth sees and trembles.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />The mountains melt like wax before Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">the Lord of the whole earth.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />The skies declare his justice,</para>
<para style="q1">and all the nations see his glory.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />All those who worship carved figures will be shamed,</para>
<para style="q1">those who boast in worthless idols—</para>
<para style="q1">bow down to him, all you gods!</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Zion heard and was glad,</para>
<para style="q1">and the towns of Judah rejoiced</para>
<para style="q1">because of your righteous decrees, Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />For you, Yahweh, are most high above all the earth.</para>
<para style="q1">You are exalted far above all gods.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />You who love Yahweh, hate evil!</para>
<para style="q1">He protects the lives of his faithful ones,</para>
<para style="q1">and he takes them out of the hand of the wicked.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />Light is sown for the righteous</para>
<para style="q1">and gladness for those with honest hearts.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />Be glad in Yahweh, you righteous;</para>
<para style="q1">and give thanks when you remember his holiness.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="98" style="c" />
<para style="d">A psalm.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Oh, sing to Yahweh a new song,</para>
<para style="q1">for he has done marvelous things;</para>
<para style="q1">his right hand and his holy arm have given him victory.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Yahweh has made known his salvation;</para>
<para style="q1">he has openly showed his justice to all the nations.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />He calls to mind his covenant loyalty and faithfulness for the house of Israel;</para>
<para style="q1">all the ends of the earth will see the victory of our God.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Shout for joy to Yahweh, all the earth;</para>
<para style="q1">burst into song, sing for joy, and sing praises.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Sing praises to Yahweh with the harp,</para>
<para style="q1">with the harp and melodious song.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />With trumpets and the sound of the horn,</para>
<para style="q1">make a joyful noise before the King, Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Let the sea shout and everything in it,</para>
<para style="q1">the world and those who live in it!</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Let the rivers clap their hands,</para>
<para style="q1">and let the mountains shout for joy.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />Yahweh is coming to judge the earth;</para>
<para style="q1">he will judge the world with righteousness</para>
<para style="q1">and the nations with fairness.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="99" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Yahweh reigns; let the nations tremble.</para>
<para style="q1">He sits enthroned above the cherubim; the earth quakes.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Yahweh is great in Zion;</para>
<para style="q1">he is exalted above all the nations.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Let them praise your great and awesome name;</para>
<para style="q1">he is holy.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />The king is strong, and he loves justice.</para>
<para style="q1">You have established fairness;</para>
<para style="q1">you have done righteousness and justice in Jacob.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Praise Yahweh our God</para>
<para style="q1">and worship at his footstool.</para>
<para style="q1">He is holy.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Moses and Aaron were among his priests,</para>
<para style="q1">and Samuel was among those who called on his name.</para>
<para style="q1">They called to Yahweh, and he answered them.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />He spoke to them from the pillar of cloud.</para>
<para style="q1">They kept his solemn commands</para>
<para style="q1">and the statutes that he gave them.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />You answered them, Yahweh our God.</para>
<para style="q1">A forgiving God you were to them,</para>
<para style="q1">but one who punished their sinful deeds.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />Praise Yahweh our God,</para>
<para style="q1">and worship at his holy hill,</para>
<para style="q1">for Yahweh our God is holy.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="100" style="c" />
<para style="d">A psalm of thanksgiving.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Shout joyfully to Yahweh, all the earth.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Serve Yahweh with gladness;</para>
<para style="q1">come before his presence with joyful singing.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Know that Yahweh is God;</para>
<para style="q1">he made us, and we are his.</para>
<para style="q1">We are his people and the sheep of his pasture.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Enter into his gates with thanksgiving</para>
<para style="q1">and into his courts with praise.</para>
<para style="q1">Give thanks to him and bless his name.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />For Yahweh is good; his covenant faithfulness endures forever</para>
<para style="q1">and his truthfulness through all generations.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="101" style="c" />
<para style="d">A psalm of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />I will sing of covenant faithfulness and justice;</para>
<para style="q1">to you, Yahweh, I will sing praises.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />I will walk in the way of integrity.</para>
<para style="q1">Oh, when will you come to me?</para>
<para style="q1">I will walk with integrity within my house.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />I will not put wrongdoing before my eyes;</para>
<para style="q1">I hate worthless evil;</para>
<para style="q1">it will not cling to me.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Perverse people will leave me;</para>
<para style="q1">I am not loyal to evil.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />I will destroy whoever secretly slanders his neighbor.</para>
<para style="q1">I will not tolerate anyone who has a proud demeanor and an arrogant attitude.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />I will look to the faithful of the land to sit at my side.</para>
<para style="q1">Those who walk in the way of integrity may serve me.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Deceitful people will not remain within my house;</para>
<para style="q1">liars will not be welcome before my eyes.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Morning by morning I will destroy all the wicked from the land;</para>
<para style="q1">I will remove all evildoers from the city of Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="102" style="c" />
<para style="d">A prayer of the afflicted when he is faint and pours out his lament before Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Hear my prayer, Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">hear my cry to you.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Do not hide your face from me in my time of trouble.</para>
<para style="q1">Listen to me.</para>
<para style="q1">When I call out to you, answer me quickly.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />For my days pass away like smoke,</para>
<para style="q1">and my bones burn like fire.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />My heart is crushed, and I am like grass that has withered.</para>
<para style="q1">I forget to eat any food.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />With my continual groaning,</para>
<para style="q1">I have become very thin.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />I am like a pelican of the wilderness;</para>
<para style="q1">I have become like an owl in the ruins.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />I lie awake like a solitary bird,</para>
<para style="q1">alone on the housetop.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />My enemies taunt me all day long;</para>
<para style="q1">those who mock me use my name in curses.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />I eat ashes like bread</para>
<para style="q1">and mix my drink with tears.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />Because of your raging anger,</para>
<para style="q1">you have lifted me up to throw me down.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />My days are like a shadow that fades,</para>
<para style="q1">and I have withered like grass.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />But you, Yahweh, live forever,</para>
<para style="q1">and your fame is for all generations.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />You will rise up and have mercy on Zion.</para>
<para style="q1">Now is the time to have mercy upon her;</para>
<para style="q1">the appointed time has come.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />For your servants hold her stones dear</para>
<para style="q1">and feel compassion for the dust of her ruins.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />The nations will respect your name, Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">and all the kings of the earth will honor your glory.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />Yahweh will rebuild Zion</para>
<para style="q1">and will appear in his glory.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />At that time, he will respond to the prayer of the destitute;</para>
<para style="q1">he will not reject their prayer.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />This will be written for future generations,</para>
<para style="q1">and a people not yet born will praise Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="19" style="v" />For he has looked down from the holy heights;</para>
<para style="q1">from heaven Yahweh has viewed the earth,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="20" style="v" />to hear the groaning of the prisoners,</para>
<para style="q1">to release those who were condemned to death.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="21" style="v" />Then men will proclaim the name of Yahweh in Zion</para>
<para style="q1">and his praise in Jerusalem</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="22" style="v" />when the peoples and kingdoms gather together</para>
<para style="q1">to serve Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="23" style="v" />He has taken away my strength in the middle of life.</para>
<para style="q1">He has shortened my days.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="24" style="v" />I said, "My God, do not take me away in the middle of life;</para>
<para style="q1">you are here throughout all generations.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="25" style="v" />In ancient times you set the earth in place;</para>
<para style="q1">the heavens are the work of your hands.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="26" style="v" />They will perish, but you will remain;</para>
<para style="q1">they will all grow old like a garment;</para>
<para style="q1">like clothing, you will remove them, and they will disappear.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="27" style="v" />But you are the same,</para>
<para style="q1">and your years will have no end.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="28" style="v" />The children of your servants will live on,</para>
<para style="q1">and their descendants will live in your presence."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="103" style="c" />
<para style="d">A psalm of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />I give praise to Yahweh with all my life,</para>
<para style="q1">and with all that is within me, I give praise to his holy name.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />I give praise to Yahweh with all my life,</para>
<para style="q1">and I remember all of his good deeds.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />He forgives all your sins;</para>
<para style="q1">he heals all your diseases.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />He redeems your life from destruction;</para>
<para style="q1">he crowns you with covenant faithfulness and acts of tender mercy.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />He satisfies your life with good things</para>
<para style="q1">so that your youth is renewed like the eagle.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Yahweh does what is fair</para>
<para style="q1">and does acts of justice for all who are oppressed.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />He made known his ways to Moses,</para>
<para style="q1">his deeds to the descendants of Israel.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Yahweh is merciful and gracious;</para>
<para style="q1">he is patient; he has great covenant loyalty.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />He will not always discipline;</para>
<para style="q1">he is not always angry.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />He does not deal with us as our sins deserve</para>
<para style="q1">or repay us for what our sins demand.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />For as the skies are high above the earth,</para>
<para style="q1">so great is his covenant faithfulness toward those who honor him.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />As far as the east is from the west,</para>
<para style="q1">this is how far he has removed the guilt of our sins from us.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />As a father has compassion on his children,</para>
<para style="q1">so Yahweh has compassion on those who honor him.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />For he knows how we are formed;</para>
<para style="q1">he knows that we are dust.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />As for man, his days are like grass;</para>
<para style="q1">he flourishes like a flower in a field.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />The wind blows over it, and it disappears,</para>
<para style="q1">and no one can even tell where it once grew.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />But the covenant faithfulness of Yahweh is from everlasting to everlasting on those who honor him.</para>
<para style="q1">His righteousness extends to their descendants.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />They keep his covenant</para>
<para style="q1">and remember to obey his instructions.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="19" style="v" />Yahweh has established his throne in the heavens,</para>
<para style="q1">and his kingdom rules over everyone.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="20" style="v" />Give praise to Yahweh, you his angels,</para>
<para style="q1">you mighty ones who are strong and do his word,</para>
<para style="q1">and obey the sound of his word.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="21" style="v" />Give praise to Yahweh, all his hosts,</para>
<para style="q1">you are his servants who carry out his will.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="22" style="v" />Give praise to Yahweh, all his creatures,</para>
<para style="q1">in all the places where he reigns.</para>
<para style="q1">I will give praise to Yahweh with all my life.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="104" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />I give praise to Yahweh with all my life,</para>
<para style="q1">Yahweh my God, you are very magnificent;</para>
<para style="q1">you are clothed with splendor and majesty.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />You cover yourself with light as with a garment;</para>
<para style="q1">you spread out the heavens like a tent curtain.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />You lay the beams of your chambers on the clouds;</para>
<para style="q1">you make the clouds your chariot;</para>
<para style="q1">you walk on the wings of the wind.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />He makes the winds his messengers,</para>
<para style="q1">flames of fire his servants.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />He laid the foundations of the earth,</para>
<para style="q1">and it will never be moved.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />You covered the earth with water like a garment;</para>
<para style="q1">the water covered the mountains.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Your rebuke made the waters recede;</para>
<para style="q1">at the sound of your thunderous voice they fled.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />The mountains rose, and the valleys spread out</para>
<para style="q1">into the places that you had appointed for them.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />You have set a boundary for them that they will not cross;</para>
<para style="q1">they will not cover the earth again.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />He made springs flow into the valleys;</para>
<para style="q1">the streams flow between the mountains.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />They supply water for all the animals of the field;</para>
<para style="q1">the wild donkeys quench their thirst.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />By the riverbanks the birds build their nests;</para>
<para style="q1">they sing among the branches.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />He waters the mountains from his water chambers in the sky.</para>
<para style="q1">The earth is filled with the fruit of his labor.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />He makes the grass grow for the cattle</para>
<para style="q1">and plants for man to cultivate</para>
<para style="q1">so that man may produce food from the earth.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />He makes wine to make man happy,</para>
<para style="q1">oil to make his face shine,</para>
<para style="q1">and food to sustain his life.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />The trees of Yahweh get plenty of rain;</para>
<para style="q1">the cedars of Lebanon which he planted.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />There the birds make their nests.</para>
<para style="q1">The stork makes the cypress tree her home.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />The wild goats live on the high mountains;</para>
<para style="q1">the mountain heights are a refuge for the hyraxes.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="19" style="v" />He appointed the moon to mark the seasons;</para>
<para style="q1">the sun knows its time for setting.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="20" style="v" />You make the darkness of the night</para>
<para style="q1">when all the beasts of the forest come out.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="21" style="v" />The young lions roar for their prey</para>
<para style="q1">and seek their food from God.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="22" style="v" />When the sun rises, they retreat</para>
<para style="q1">and sleep in their dens.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="23" style="v" />Meanwhile, people go out to their work</para>
<para style="q1">and labor away until the evening.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="24" style="v" />Yahweh, how many and varied are your works!</para>
<para style="q1">With wisdom you made them all;</para>
<para style="q1">the earth overflows with your works.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="25" style="v" />Over there is the sea, deep and wide,</para>
<para style="q1">teeming with innumerable creatures,</para>
<para style="q1">both small and great.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="26" style="v" />The ships travel there,</para>
<para style="q1">and Leviathan is also there, which you formed to play in the sea.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="27" style="v" />All these look to you to give them</para>
<para style="q1">their food on time.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="28" style="v" />When you give to them, they gather;</para>
<para style="q1">when you open your hand, they are satisfied.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="29" style="v" />When you hide your face, they are troubled;</para>
<para style="q1">if you take away their breath, they die</para>
<para style="q1">and return to dust.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="30" style="v" />When you send out your Spirit, they are created,</para>
<para style="q1">and you renew the countryside.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="31" style="v" />May the glory of Yahweh last forever;</para>
<para style="q1">may Yahweh enjoy his creation.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="32" style="v" />He looks down on the earth, and it shakes;</para>
<para style="q1">he touches the mountains, and they smoke.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="33" style="v" />I will sing to Yahweh all my life;</para>
<para style="q1">I will sing praise to my God as long as I live.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="34" style="v" />May my thoughts be sweet to him;</para>
<para style="q1">I will rejoice in Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="35" style="v" />May sinners vanish from the earth,</para>
<para style="q1">and let the wicked be no more.</para>
<para style="q1">I give praise to Yahweh with all my life.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="105" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Give thanks to Yahweh, call on his name;</para>
<para style="q1">make known his deeds among the nations.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Sing to him, sing praises to him;</para>
<para style="q1">speak of all his marvelous deeds.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Boast in his holy name;</para>
<para style="q1">let the heart of those who seek Yahweh rejoice.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Seek Yahweh and his strength;</para>
<para style="q1">seek his presence continually.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Recall the marvelous things he has done,</para>
<para style="q1">his miracles and the decrees from his mouth,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />you descendants of Abraham his servant,</para>
<para style="q1">you people of Jacob, his chosen ones.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />He is Yahweh, our God.</para>
<para style="q1">His decrees are on all the earth.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />He keeps in mind his covenant forever,</para>
<para style="q1">the word that he commanded for a thousand generations.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />He calls to mind the covenant that he made with Abraham</para>
<para style="q1">and his oath to Isaac.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />This is what he confirmed to Jacob as a statute</para>
<para style="q1">and to Israel as an everlasting covenant.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />He said, "I will give you the land of Canaan</para>
<para style="q1">as your share of your inheritance."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />He said this when they were only few in number,</para>
<para style="q1">so very few, and were strangers in the land.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />They went from nation to nation</para>
<para style="q1">and from one kingdom to another.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />He did not allow anyone to oppress them;</para>
<para style="q1">he rebuked kings for their sakes.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />He said, "Do not touch my anointed ones,</para>
<para style="q1">and do not harm my prophets."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />He called for a famine on the land;</para>
<para style="q1">he cut off the whole supply of bread.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />He sent a man ahead of them;</para>
<para style="q1">Joseph was sold as a servant.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />His feet were bound by shackles;</para>
<para style="q1">on his neck was put an iron collar,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="19" style="v" />until what he had said came to pass.</para>
<para style="q1">The word of Yahweh tested him.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="20" style="v" />The king sent servants to release him;</para>
<para style="q1">the ruler of the people set him free.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="21" style="v" />He put him in charge of his house</para>
<para style="q1">as ruler of all his possessions</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="22" style="v" />to instruct his princes as he wished</para>
<para style="q1">and to teach his elders wisdom.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="23" style="v" />Then Israel came into Egypt,</para>
<para style="q1">and Jacob lived for a time in the land of Ham.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="24" style="v" />Yahweh made his people fruitful,</para>
<para style="q1">and made them stronger than their enemies.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="25" style="v" />He caused their enemies to hate his people,</para>
<para style="q1">to mistreat his servants.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="26" style="v" />He sent Moses, his servant,</para>
<para style="q1">and Aaron, whom he had chosen.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="27" style="v" />They performed his signs among the Egyptians,</para>
<para style="q1">his wonders in the land of Ham.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="28" style="v" />He sent darkness and made that land dark,</para>
<para style="q1">but its people did not obey his commands.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="29" style="v" />He turned their water into blood</para>
<para style="q1">and killed their fish.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="30" style="v" />Their land swarmed with frogs,</para>
<para style="q1">even in the rooms of their rulers.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="31" style="v" />He spoke, and swarms of flies and gnats came</para>
<para style="q1">throughout their country.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="32" style="v" />He turned their rain into hail,</para>
<para style="q1">with fire flaming on their land.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="33" style="v" />He destroyed their vines and fig trees;</para>
<para style="q1">he broke the trees of their country.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="34" style="v" />He spoke, and the locusts came,</para>
<para style="q1">so many locusts.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="35" style="v" />The locusts ate up all of the vegetation in their land;</para>
<para style="q1">They ate up all the crops of the ground.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="36" style="v" />He killed every firstborn in their land,</para>
<para style="q1">the firstfruits of all their strength.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="37" style="v" />He brought the Israelites out with silver and gold;</para>
<para style="q1">none of his tribes stumbled on the way.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="38" style="v" />Egypt was glad when they went away,</para>
<para style="q1">for the Egyptians were afraid of them.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="39" style="v" />He spread a cloud for a covering</para>
<para style="q1">and made a fire to light up the night.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="40" style="v" />The Israelites asked for food, and he brought quail</para>
<para style="q1">and satisfied them with bread from heaven.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="41" style="v" />He split the rock, and waters gushed from it;</para>
<para style="q1">they flowed in the wilderness like a river.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="42" style="v" />For he called to mind his holy promise</para>
<para style="q1">that he made to Abraham his servant.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="43" style="v" />He led his people out with joy,</para>
<para style="q1">his chosen with shouts of triumph.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="44" style="v" />He gave them the lands of the nations;</para>
<para style="q1">they took possession of the wealth of the peoples</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="45" style="v" />so that they might keep his statutes</para>
<para style="q1">and obey his laws.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="106" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Praise Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">Give thanks to Yahweh, for he is good,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Who can recount the mighty acts of Yahweh</para>
<para style="q1">or proclaim in full all his praiseworthy deeds?
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Blessed are those who do what is right,</para>
<para style="q1">and whose deeds are always just.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Call me to mind, Yahweh, when you show favor to your people;</para>
<para style="q1">help me when you save them.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Then I will see the prosperity of your chosen,</para>
<para style="q1">rejoice in the gladness of your nation,</para>
<para style="q1">and glory with your inheritance.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />We have sinned like our ancestors;</para>
<para style="q1">we have done wrong, and we have done evil.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Our fathers did not appreciate your marvelous deeds in Egypt;</para>
<para style="q1">they ignored your many acts of covenant faithfulness;</para>
<para style="q1">they were rebellious at the sea, the Sea of Reeds.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Nevertheless, he saved them for his name's sake</para>
<para style="q1">so that he might reveal his power.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />He rebuked the Sea of Reeds, and it dried up.</para>
<para style="q1">Then he led them through the depths, as through a wilderness.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />He saved them from the hand of those who hated them,</para>
<para style="q1">and he rescued them from the hand of the enemy.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />But the waters covered their adversaries;</para>
<para style="q1">not one of them survived.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />Then they believed his words,</para>
<para style="q1">and they sang his praise.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />But they quickly forgot what he had done;</para>
<para style="q1">they did not wait for his instructions.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />They had insatiable cravings in the wilderness,</para>
<para style="q1">and they challenged God in the desert.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />So he gave them what they requested,</para>
<para style="q2">but he sent a horrible disease upon them.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />In the camp they became jealous of Moses</para>
<para style="q1">and Aaron, the holy priest of Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />The earth opened and swallowed up Dathan</para>
<para style="q1">and covered the followers of Abiram.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />Fire broke out among them;</para>
<para style="q1">the fire consumed the wicked.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="19" style="v" />They made a calf at Horeb</para>
<para style="q1">and worshiped a cast metal figure.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="20" style="v" />They traded the glory of God</para>
<para style="q1">for the image of a bull that eats grass.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="21" style="v" />They forgot God their Savior,</para>
<para style="q1">who had done great deeds in Egypt.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="22" style="v" />He had done wonderful things in the land of Ham</para>
<para style="q1">and mighty acts at the Sea of Reeds.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="23" style="v" />So he said he would destroy them—</para>
<para style="q1">had not Moses, his chosen one, stood in the breach before him,</para>
<para style="q1">to turn away his anger from destroying them.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="24" style="v" />Then they despised the fruitful land;</para>
<para style="q1">they did not believe his promise,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="25" style="v" />but grumbled in their tents,</para>
<para style="q1">and did not obey Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="26" style="v" />Therefore he raised his hand and swore to them</para>
<para style="q1">that he would let them die in the desert,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="27" style="v" />scatter their descendants among the nations,</para>
<para style="q1">and scatter them in foreign lands.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="28" style="v" />They worshiped the Baal of Peor</para>
<para style="q1">and ate the sacrifices offered to the dead.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="29" style="v" />They provoked him to anger with their actions,</para>
<para style="q1">and a plague broke out among them.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="30" style="v" />Then Phinehas rose to intervene,</para>
<para style="q1">and the plague subsided.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="31" style="v" />It was counted to him as a righteous deed</para>
<para style="q1">to all generations forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="32" style="v" />They also angered Yahweh at the waters of Meribah,</para>
<para style="q1">and Moses suffered because of them.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="33" style="v" />They made Moses bitter,</para>
<para style="q1">and he spoke rashly.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="34" style="v" />They did not destroy the nations</para>
<para style="q1">as Yahweh had commanded them,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="35" style="v" />but they mingled with the nations</para>
<para style="q1">and learned their ways</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="36" style="v" />and worshiped their idols,</para>
<para style="q1">which became a snare to them.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="37" style="v" />They sacrificed their sons and their daughters to demons.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="38" style="v" />They shed innocent blood,</para>
<para style="q1">the blood of their sons and of their daughters,</para>
<para style="q1">whom they sacrificed to the idols of Canaan,</para>
<para style="q1">desecrating the land with blood.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="39" style="v" />They were defiled by their deeds;</para>
<para style="q1">in their actions they were like prostitutes.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="40" style="v" />So Yahweh was angry with his people,</para>
<para style="q1">and he despised his own people.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="41" style="v" />He gave them into the hand of the nations,</para>
<para style="q1">and those who hated them ruled over them.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="42" style="v" />Their enemies oppressed them,</para>
<para style="q1">and they were brought into subjection to their authority.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="43" style="v" />Many times he came to help them,</para>
<para style="q1">but they kept rebelling</para>
<para style="q1">and were brought low by their own sin.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="44" style="v" />Nevertheless, he paid attention to their distress</para>
<para style="q1">when he heard their cry for help.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="45" style="v" />He called to mind his covenant with them</para>
<para style="q1">and relented because of his steadfast love.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="46" style="v" />He caused all their conquerers</para>
<para style="q1">to have pity on them.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="47" style="v" />Save us, Yahweh, our God.</para>
<para style="q1">Gather us from among the nations</para>
<para style="q1">so that we may give thanks to your holy name</para>
<para style="q1">and glory in your praises.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="48" style="v" />May Yahweh, the God of Israel, be praised</para>
<para style="q1">from everlasting to everlasting.</para>
<para style="q1">All the people said, "Amen."</para>
<para style="q1">Praise Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="ms">Book Five</para>
<chapter number="107" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Give thanks to Yahweh, for he is good,</para>
<para style="q1">and his covenant faithfulness endures forever.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Let the redeemed of Yahweh speak out,</para>
<para style="q1">those he has rescued from the hand of the enemy.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />He has gathered them out of foreign lands,</para>
<para style="q1">from the east and from the west,</para>
<para style="q1">from the north and from the south.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />They wandered in the wilderness on a desert road</para>
<para style="q1">and found no city in which to live.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Because they were hungry and thirsty,</para>
<para style="q1">they fainted from exhaustion.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Then they called out to Yahweh in their trouble,</para>
<para style="q1">and he rescued them out of their distress.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />He led them by a direct path</para>
<para style="q1">so that they would go to a city to live in.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Oh that people would praise Yahweh for his covenant faithfulness</para>
<para style="q1">and for the amazing things he has done for humanity!</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />For he satisfies the longings of those who are thirsty,</para>
<para style="q1">and the desires of those who are hungry he fills up with good things.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />Some sat in darkness and in gloom,</para>
<para style="q1">prisoners in affliction and chains.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />This was because they had rebelled against God's word</para>
<para style="q1">and rejected the instruction of the Most High.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />He humbled their hearts through hardship;</para>
<para style="q1">they stumbled and there was no one to help them up.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />Then they called out to Yahweh in their trouble,</para>
<para style="q1">and he brought them out of their distress.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />He brought them out of darkness and gloom</para>
<para style="q1">and broke their bonds.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />Oh that people would praise Yahweh for his covenant faithfulness</para>
<para style="q1">and for the amazing things he has done for humanity!</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />For he has broken the gates of bronze</para>
<para style="q1">and cut through the bars of iron.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />They were foolish in their rebellious ways</para>
<para style="q1">and afflicted because of their sins.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />They lost their desire to eat any food,</para>
<para style="q1">and they came close to the gates of death.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="19" style="v" />Then they called out to Yahweh in their trouble,</para>
<para style="q1">and he brought them out of their distress.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="20" style="v" />He sent his word and healed them,</para>
<para style="q1">and he rescued them from their destruction.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="21" style="v" />Oh that people would praise Yahweh for his covenant faithfulness</para>
<para style="q1">and for the amazing things he has done for humanity!</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="22" style="v" />Let them offer the sacrifices of thanksgiving</para>
<para style="q1">and proclaim his deeds in singing.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="23" style="v" />Some travel on the sea in ships</para>
<para style="q1">and do business overseas.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="24" style="v" />These saw the deeds of Yahweh</para>
<para style="q1">and his wonders on the seas.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="25" style="v" />For he commanded and aroused the windstorm</para>
<para style="q1">that stirs up the seas.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="26" style="v" />They reached up to the sky; they went down to the depths.</para>
<para style="q1">Their lives melted away in distress.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="27" style="v" />They swayed and staggered like drunkards</para>
<para style="q1">and were at their wits' end.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="28" style="v" />Then they called out to Yahweh in their trouble,</para>
<para style="q1">and he brought them out of their distress.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="29" style="v" />He calmed the storm,</para>
<para style="q1">and the waves were stilled.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="30" style="v" />Then they rejoiced because the sea was calm,</para>
<para style="q1">and he brought them to their desired harbor.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="31" style="v" />Oh that people would praise Yahweh for his covenant faithfulness</para>
<para style="q1">and for the amazing things he has done for humanity!</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="32" style="v" />Let them exalt him in the assembly of the people</para>
<para style="q1">and praise him in the council of the elders.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="33" style="v" />He turns rivers into a wilderness,</para>
<para style="q1">springs of water into dry land,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="34" style="v" />and a fruitful land into a barren place</para>
<para style="q1">because of the wickedness of its people.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="35" style="v" />He turns the wilderness into a pool of water</para>
<para style="q1">and dry land into springs of water.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="36" style="v" />He settles the hungry there,</para>
<para style="q1">and they build a city to live in.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="37" style="v" />They build a city to plant fields in, to plant vineyards,</para>
<para style="q1">and to bring in an abundant harvest.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="38" style="v" />He blesses them so they are very numerous.</para>
<para style="q1">He does not let their cattle decrease in number.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="39" style="v" />They were diminished and brought low</para>
<para style="q1">by painful distress and suffering.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="40" style="v" />He pours contempt on the leaders</para>
<para style="q1">and causes them to wander in the wilderness, where there are no roads.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="41" style="v" />But he protects the needy from affliction</para>
<para style="q1">and cares for his families like a flock.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="42" style="v" />The upright will see this and rejoice,</para>
<para style="q1">and all wickedness shuts its mouth.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="43" style="v" />Whoever is wise should take note of these things</para>
<para style="q1">and meditate on Yahweh's acts of covenant faithfulness.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="108" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song, a psalm of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />My heart is fixed, God;</para>
<para style="q1">I will sing, yes, I will sing praises also with my honored heart.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Wake up, lute and harp;</para>
<para style="q1">I will wake up the dawn.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />I will give thanks to you, Yahweh, among the peoples;</para>
<para style="q1">I will sing praises to you among the nations.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />For your covenant faithfulness is great above the heavens;</para>
<para style="q1">and your trustworthiness reaches to the skies.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Be exalted, God, above the heavens,</para>
<para style="q1">and may your glory be exalted over all the earth.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />So that those you love may be rescued,</para>
<para style="q1">rescue us with your right hand and answer me.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />God has spoken in his holiness; "I will rejoice;</para>
<para style="q1">I will divide Shechem and apportion out the Valley of Succoth.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Gilead is mine, and Manasseh is mine;</para>
<para style="q1">Ephraim also is my helmet;</para>
<para style="q1">Judah is my scepter.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />Moab is my washbasin;</para>
<para style="q1">over Edom I will throw my shoe;</para>
<para style="q1">I will shout in triumph because of Philistia.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />Who will bring me into the strong city?</para>
<para style="q1">Who will lead me to Edom?"
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />God, have you not rejected us?</para>
<para style="q1">You do not go into battle with our army.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />Give us help against the enemy,</para>
<para style="q1">for man's help is futile.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />We will triumph with God's help;</para>
<para style="q1">he will trample down our enemies.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="109" style="c" />
<para style="d">For the chief musician. A psalm of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />God whom I praise, do not be silent,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />For the wicked and deceitful attack me;</para>
<para style="q1">they speak lies against me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />They surround me and say hateful things,</para>
<para style="q1">and they attack me without cause.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />In return for my love they accuse me,</para>
<para style="q1">but I pray for them.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />They repay me evil for good,</para>
<para style="q1">and they hate my love.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Appoint a wicked man over such an enemy as these people;</para>
<para style="q1">appoint an accuser to stand at his right hand.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />When he is judged, may he be found guilty;</para>
<para style="q1">may his prayer be considered sinful.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />May his days be few;</para>
<para style="q1">may another take his office.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />May his children be fatherless,</para>
<para style="q1">and may his wife be a widow.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />May his children wander about and beg,</para>
<para style="q1">asking for handouts as they leave their ruined home.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />May the creditor take all he owns;</para>
<para style="q1">may strangers plunder what he earns.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />May no one extend any kindness to him;</para>
<para style="q1">may no one have pity on his fatherless children.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />May his children be cut off;</para>
<para style="q1">may their name be blotted out in the next generation.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />May his ancestors' sins be mentioned to Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">and may the sin of his mother not be forgotten.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />May their guilt always be before Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">may Yahweh cut off their memory from the earth.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />May Yahweh do this because this man never bothered to show any covenant faithfulness,</para>
<para style="q1">but instead harassed the oppressed, the needy,</para>
<para style="q1">and the disheartened to death.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />He loved cursing; may it come back upon him.</para>
<para style="q1">He hated blessing; may no blessing come to him.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />He clothed himself with cursing as his garment,</para>
<para style="q1">and his curse came into his inner being like water,</para>
<para style="q1">like oil into his bones.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="19" style="v" />May his curses be to him like the clothes he wears to cover himself,</para>
<para style="q1">like the belt he always wears.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="20" style="v" />May this be the reward of my accusers from Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">of those who say evil things about me.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="21" style="v" />Yahweh my Lord, deal kindly with me for your name's sake.</para>
<para style="q1">Because your covenant faithfulness is good, save me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="22" style="v" />For I am oppressed and needy,</para>
<para style="q1">and my heart is wounded within me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="23" style="v" />I am fading away like the shadow of the evening;</para>
<para style="q1">I am shaken off like a locust.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="24" style="v" />My knees are weak from fasting;</para>
<para style="q1">I am turning to skin and bones.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="25" style="v" />I am disdained by my accusers;</para>
<para style="q1">when they see me, they shake their heads.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="26" style="v" />Help me, Yahweh my God;</para>
<para style="q1">save me by your covenant faithfulness.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="27" style="v" />May they know that this is your doing,</para>
<para style="q1">that you, Yahweh, have done this.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="28" style="v" />Though they curse me, please bless me;</para>
<para style="q1">when they attack, may they be put to shame,</para>
<para style="q1">but may your servant rejoice.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="29" style="v" />May my adversaries be clothed with shame;</para>
<para style="q1">may they wear their shame like a robe.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="30" style="v" />With my mouth I give great thanks to Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">I will praise him in the midst of a crowd.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="31" style="v" />For he will stand at the right hand of the one who is needy,</para>
<para style="q1">to save him from those who judge him.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="110" style="c" />
<para style="d">A psalm of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Yahweh says to my master, "Sit at my right hand</para>
<para style="q1">until I make your enemies your footstool."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Yahweh will hold out the scepter of your strength from Zion;</para>
<para style="q1">rule among your enemies.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Your people will follow you in holy garments</para>
<para style="q1">of their own free will on the day of your power;</para>
<para style="q1">from the womb of the dawn your youth will be to you like the dew.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Yahweh has sworn, and will not change:</para>
<para style="q1">"You are a priest forever,</para>
<para style="q1">after the manner of Melchizedek."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />The Lord is at your right hand.</para>
<para style="q1">He will kill kings on the day of his anger.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />He will judge the nations;</para>
<para style="q1">he will fill the battlegrounds with dead bodies;</para>
<para style="q1">he will kill the leaders in many countries.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />He will drink of the brook along the road,</para>
<para style="q1">and then he will lift his head up high after victory.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="111" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Praise Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">I will give thanks to Yahweh with my whole heart</para>
<para style="q1">in the assembly of the upright, in their gathering.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />The works of Yahweh are great,</para>
<para style="q1">eagerly awaited by all those who desire them.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />His work is majestic and glorious,</para>
<para style="q1">and his righteousness endures forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />He does wonderful things that will be remembered;</para>
<para style="q1">Yahweh is gracious and merciful.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />He gives food to his faithful followers.</para>
<para style="q1">He will always call to mind his covenant.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />He showed his powerful works to his people</para>
<para style="q1">in giving them the inheritance of the nations.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />The works of his hands are trustworthy and just;</para>
<para style="q1">all his instructions are reliable.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />They are established forever,</para>
<para style="q1">to be observed faithfully and properly.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />He gave victory to his people;</para>
<para style="q1">he ordained his covenant forever;</para>
<para style="q1">holy and awesome is his name.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />To honor Yahweh is the beginning of wisdom;</para>
<para style="q1">those who carry out his instructions have good understanding.</para>
<para style="q1">His praise endures forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="112" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Praise Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">Blessed is the man who fears Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">who greatly delights in his commandments.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />His descendants will be powerful on earth;</para>
<para style="q1">the descendants of the godly man will be blessed.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Wealth and riches are in his house;</para>
<para style="q1">his righteousness will endure forever.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Light shines in the darkness for the godly person;</para>
<para style="q1">he is gracious, merciful, and just.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />It goes well for the man who deals graciously and lends money,</para>
<para style="q1">who conducts his affairs with honesty.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />For he will never be moved;</para>
<para style="q1">the righteous person will be remembered forever.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />He does not fear bad news;</para>
<para style="q1">he is confident, trusting in Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />His heart is tranquil, without fear,</para>
<para style="q1">until he looks in triumph over his adversaries.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />He generously gives to the poor;</para>
<para style="q1">his righteousness endures forever;</para>
<para style="q1">he will be exalted with honor.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />The wicked person will see this and be angry;</para>
<para style="q1">he will grind his teeth in rage and he will melt away;</para>
<para style="q1">the desire of the wicked people will perish.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="113" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Praise Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise him, you servants of Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">praise the name of Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Blessed be the name of Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">both now and forevermore.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />From the rising of the sun to its setting,</para>
<para style="q1">Yahweh's name should be praised.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Yahweh is exalted above all nations,</para>
<para style="q1">and his glory reaches above the skies.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Who is like Yahweh our God,</para>
<para style="q1">who has his seat on high,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />who looks down</para>
<para style="q1">at the sky and at the earth?
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />He raises up the poor out of the dirt</para>
<para style="q1">and lifts up the needy from the ash heap,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />so that he may seat him with princes,</para>
<para style="q1">with the princes of his people.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />He gives a home to the barren woman of the house,</para>
<para style="q1">he makes her a joyful mother of children.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise Yahweh!
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="114" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />When Israel left Egypt,</para>
<para style="q1">the house of Jacob from a people who spoke a foreign language,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Judah became his holy place,</para>
<para style="q1">Israel his kingdom.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />The sea looked and fled;</para>
<para style="q1">the Jordan turned back.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />The mountains skipped like rams,</para>
<para style="q1">the hills skipped like lambs.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Why did you flee, sea?</para>
<para style="q1">Jordan, why did you turn back?</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Mountains, why did you skip like rams?</para>
<para style="q1">You little hills, why did you skip like lambs?</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Tremble, earth, before the Lord,</para>
<para style="q1">at the presence of the God of Jacob.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />He turned the rock into a pool of water,</para>
<para style="q1">the hard rock into a spring of water.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="115" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Not to us, Yahweh, not to us,</para>
<para style="q1">but to your name bring honor,</para>
<para style="q1">for your covenant faithfulness and for your trustworthiness.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Why should the nations say,</para>
<para style="q1">"Where is their God?"
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Our God is in heaven;</para>
<para style="q1">he does whatever he pleases.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />The nations' idols are silver and gold,</para>
<para style="q1">the work of men's hands.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Those idols have mouths, but they do not speak;</para>
<para style="q1">they have eyes, but they do not see;</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />they have ears, but they do not hear;</para>
<para style="q1">they have noses, but they do not smell.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Those idols have hands, but do not feel;</para>
<para style="q1">they have feet, but they cannot walk;</para>
<para style="q1">nor do they speak from their mouths.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Those who make them are like them,</para>
<para style="q1">as is everyone who trusts in them.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />Israel, trust in Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">he is your help and shield.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />House of Aaron, trust in Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">he is your help and shield.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />You who honor Yahweh, trust in him;</para>
<para style="q1">he is your help and shield.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />Yahweh takes notice of us and will bless us;</para>
<para style="q1">he will bless the family of Israel;</para>
<para style="q1">he will bless the family of Aaron.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />He will bless those who honor him,</para>
<para style="q1">both young and old.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />May Yahweh increase your numbers more and more,</para>
<para style="q1">yours and your descendants'.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />May you be blessed by Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">who made heaven and earth.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />The heavens belong to Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">but the earth he has given to mankind.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />The dead do not praise Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">nor do any who go down into silence;</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />But we will bless Yahweh</para>
<para style="q1">now and forevermore.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="116" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />I love Yahweh because he hears</para>
<para style="q1">my voice and my pleas for mercy.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Because he listened to me,</para>
<para style="q1">I will call on him as long as I live.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />The cords of death surrounded me,</para>
<para style="q1">and the snares of Sheol confronted me;</para>
<para style="q1">I felt anguish and sorrow.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Then I called on the name of Yahweh:</para>
<para style="q1">"Please Yahweh, rescue my life."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Yahweh is merciful and fair;</para>
<para style="q1">our God is compassionate.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Yahweh protects the naive;</para>
<para style="q1">I was brought low, and he saved me.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />My soul can return to its resting place,</para>
<para style="q1">for Yahweh has been good to me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />For you rescued my life from death,</para>
<para style="q1">my eyes from tears,</para>
<para style="q1">and my feet from stumbling.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />I will serve Yahweh</para>
<para style="q1">in the land of the living.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />I believed in him, even when I said,</para>
<para style="q1">"I am greatly afflicted."</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />In my confusion I said,</para>
<para style="q1">"All men are liars."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />How can I repay Yahweh</para>
<para style="q1">for all his kindnesses to me?</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />I will raise the cup of salvation,</para>
<para style="q1">and call on the name of Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />I will fulfill my vows to Yahweh</para>
<para style="q1">in the presence of all his people.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />Precious in the sight of Yahweh</para>
<para style="q1">is the death of his faithful ones.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />Yahweh, indeed, I am your servant;</para>
<para style="q1">I am your servant, the son of your servant woman;</para>
<para style="q1">you have taken away my bonds.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />I will offer to you the sacrifice of thanksgiving</para>
<para style="q1">and will call on the name of Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />I will fulfill my vows to Yahweh</para>
<para style="q1">in the presence of all his people,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="19" style="v" />in the courts of Yahweh's house,</para>
<para style="q1">in your midst, Jerusalem.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="117" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Praise Yahweh, all you nations;</para>
<para style="q1">exalt him, all you peoples.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />For his covenant faithfulness is great toward us,</para>
<para style="q1">and the trustworthiness of Yahweh endures forever.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="118" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Give thanks to Yahweh, for he is good,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Let Israel say,</para>
<para style="q1">"His covenant faithfulness endures forever."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Let the house of Aaron say,</para>
<para style="q1">"His covenant faithfulness endures forever."</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Let the loyal followers of Yahweh say,</para>
<para style="q1">"His covenant faithfulness endures for ever."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />In my distress I called out to Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">Yahweh answered me and set me free.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Yahweh is with me; I will not be afraid;</para>
<para style="q1">what can man do to me?</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Yahweh is on my side as my helper;</para>
<para style="q1">I will look in triumph on those who hate me.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />It is better to take shelter in Yahweh</para>
<para style="q1">than to put confidence in man.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />It is better to take refuge in Yahweh</para>
<para style="q1">than to put one's trust in a princes.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />All the nations surrounded me;</para>
<para style="q1">in Yahweh's name I cut them off.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />They surrounded me; yes, they surrounded me;</para>
<para style="q1">in Yahweh's name I cut them off.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />They surrounded me like bees;</para>
<para style="q1">they disappeared as quickly as fire among thorns;</para>
<para style="q1">in Yahweh's name I cut them off.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />They attacked me to knock me down,</para>
<para style="q1">but Yahweh helped me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />Yahweh is my strength and joy,</para>
<para style="q1">and he is the one who rescues me.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />The joyful shout of victory is heard in the tents of the righteous;</para>
<para style="q1">the right hand of Yahweh conquers.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />The right hand of Yahweh is exalted;</para>
<para style="q1">the right hand of Yahweh conquers.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />I will not die, but live</para>
<para style="q1">and declare the deeds of Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />Yahweh has punished me harshly;</para>
<para style="q1">but he has not handed me over to death.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="19" style="v" />Open to me the gates of righteousness;</para>
<para style="q1">I will enter them and I will give thanks to Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="20" style="v" />This is the gate of Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">the righteous enter through it.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="21" style="v" />I will give thanks to you, for you answered me,</para>
<para style="q1">and you have become my salvation.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="22" style="v" />The stone that the builders rejected</para>
<para style="q1">has become the cornerstone.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="23" style="v" />This is Yahweh's doing;</para>
<para style="q1">it is marvelous in our eyes.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="24" style="v" />This is the day on which Yahweh has acted;</para>
<para style="q1">we will rejoice and be glad in it.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="25" style="v" />Please, Yahweh, give us victory!</para>
<para style="q1">Please, Yahweh, give us success!
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="26" style="v" />Blessed is he who comes in the name of Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">we bless you from the house of Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="27" style="v" />Yahweh is God, and he has given us light;</para>
<para style="q1">bind the sacrifice with cords to the horns of the altar.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="28" style="v" />You are my God, and I will give thanks to you;</para>
<para style="q1">you are my God; I will exalt you.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="29" style="v" />Oh, give thanks to Yahweh; for he is good;</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="119" style="c" />
<para style="qa"></para>ALEPH
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Blessed are those whose ways are blameless,</para>
<para style="q1">who walk in the law of Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Blessed are they who keep his solemn commands,</para>
<para style="q1">who seek him with all their heart.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />They do no wrong;</para>
<para style="q1">they walk in his ways.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />You have commanded us to keep your instructions</para>
<para style="q1">so that we should carefully observe them.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Oh, that I would be firmly established</para>
<para style="q1">in the observance of your statutes!</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Then I would not be put to shame</para>
<para style="q1">when I think of all your commandments.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />I will give thanks to you with an upright heart</para>
<para style="q1">when I learn your righteous decrees.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />I will observe your statutes;</para>
<para style="q1">do not leave me alone.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>BETH
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />How can a young person keep his path pure?</para>
<para style="q1">By obeying your word.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />With my whole heart I seek you;</para>
<para style="q1">Do not let me stray from your commandments.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />I have stored up your word in my heart</para>
<para style="q1">so that I might not sin against you.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />Blessed you are, Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">teach me your statutes.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />With my mouth I have declared</para>
<para style="q1">all the righteous decrees that you have revealed.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />I rejoice in the way of your covenant decrees</para>
<para style="q1">more than in all riches.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />I will meditate on your instructions</para>
<para style="q1">and pay attention to your ways.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />I delight in your statutes;</para>
<para style="q1">I will not forget your word.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>GIMEL
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />Be kind to your servant so that I may live</para>
<para style="q1">and keep your word.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />Open my eyes so that I may see</para>
<para style="q1">marvelous things in your law.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="19" style="v" />I am a foreigner in the land;</para>
<para style="q1">do not hide your commandments from me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="20" style="v" />My desires are crushed by the longing to know</para>
<para style="q1">your righteous decrees at all times.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="21" style="v" />You rebuke the proud, who are cursed,</para>
<para style="q1">who wander from your commandments.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="22" style="v" />Spare me from disgrace and humiliation,</para>
<para style="q1">for I have obeyed your covenant decrees.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="23" style="v" />Though rulers plot and slander me,</para>
<para style="q1">your servant meditates on your statutes.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="24" style="v" />Your covenant decrees are my delight,</para>
<para style="q1">and they are my counselors.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>DALETH
<para style="q1">
<verse number="25" style="v" />My life clings to the dust!</para>
<para style="q1">Give me life by your word.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="26" style="v" />I told you my ways, and you answered me;</para>
<para style="q1">teach me your statutes.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="27" style="v" />Make me understand the ways of your instructions,</para>
<para style="q1">so that I can meditate on your wondrous teachings.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="28" style="v" />I am overwhelmed with grief!</para>
<para style="q1">Strengthen me by your word.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="29" style="v" />Turn from me the path of deceit;</para>
<para style="q1">graciously teach me your law.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="30" style="v" />I have chosen the way of faithfulness;</para>
<para style="q1">I have always kept your righteous decrees before me.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="31" style="v" />I cling to your covenant decrees;</para>
<para style="q1">Yahweh, do not let me be shamed.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="32" style="v" />I will run in the path of your commandments,</para>
<para style="q1">for you enlarge my heart to do so.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>HE
<para style="q1">
<verse number="33" style="v" />Teach me, Yahweh, the way of your statutes,</para>
<para style="q1">and I will keep them to the end.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="34" style="v" />Give me understanding, and I will keep your law;</para>
<para style="q1">I will observe it with all my heart.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="35" style="v" />Guide me in the path of your commandments,</para>
<para style="q1">for I delight to walk in it.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="36" style="v" />Direct my heart toward your covenant decrees</para>
<para style="q1">and away from unrighteous gain.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="37" style="v" />Turn my eyes from looking at worthless things;</para>
<para style="q1">revive me in your ways.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="38" style="v" />Carry out for your servant your promise</para>
<para style="q1">that you made to those who honor you.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="39" style="v" />Take away the insults I dread,</para>
<para style="q1">for your righteous judgments are good.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="40" style="v" />See, I have longed for your instructions;</para>
<para style="q1">revive me in your righteousness.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>VAV
<para style="q1">
<verse number="41" style="v" />Yahweh, give me your unfailing love—</para>
<para style="q1">your salvation, according to your promise;</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="42" style="v" />then I will have a reply for the one who mocks me,</para>
<para style="q1">for I trust in your word.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="43" style="v" />Do not take the word of truth from my mouth,</para>
<para style="q1">for my hope is in your righteous decrees.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="44" style="v" />I will observe your law continually,</para>
<para style="q1">forever and ever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="45" style="v" />I will walk securely,</para>
<para style="q1">for I seek your instructions.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="46" style="v" />I will speak of your solemn commands before kings</para>
<para style="q1">and will not be ashamed.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="47" style="v" />I delight in your commandments,</para>
<para style="q1">which I love dearly.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="48" style="v" />I will lift up my hands to your commandments, which I love;</para>
<para style="q1">I will meditate on your statutes.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>ZAYIN
<para style="q1">
<verse number="49" style="v" />Call to mind your promise to your servant</para>
<para style="q1">because you have given me hope.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="50" style="v" />This is my comfort in my affliction:</para>
<para style="q1">that your promise has kept me alive.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="51" style="v" />The proud have scoffed at me,</para>
<para style="q1">yet I have not turned away from your law.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="52" style="v" />I have thought about your righteous decrees from ancient times, Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">and I comfort myself.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="53" style="v" />Hot anger has taken hold of me</para>
<para style="q1">because of the wicked who reject your law.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="54" style="v" />Your statutes have been my songs</para>
<para style="q1">in the house where I temporarily live.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="55" style="v" />I think about your name during the night, Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">and I keep your law.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="56" style="v" />This has been my practice</para>
<para style="q1">because I have observed your instructions.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>HETH
<para style="q1">
<verse number="57" style="v" />Yahweh is my portion;</para>
<para style="q1">I have determined to observe your words.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="58" style="v" />I earnestly request your favor with my whole heart;</para>
<para style="q1">be merciful to me, as your word promised.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="59" style="v" />I examined my ways</para>
<para style="q1">and turned my feet to your covenant decrees.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="60" style="v" />I hurry and do not delay</para>
<para style="q1">to keep your commandments.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="61" style="v" />The cords of the wicked have ensnared me;</para>
<para style="q1">I have not forgotten your law.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="62" style="v" />At midnight I rise to give thanks to you</para>
<para style="q1">because of your righteous decrees.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="63" style="v" />I am a companion of all who honor you,</para>
<para style="q1">to all who observe your instructions.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="64" style="v" />The earth, Yahweh, is full of your covenant faithfulness;</para>
<para style="q1">teach me your statutes.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>TETH
<para style="q1">
<verse number="65" style="v" />You have done good to your servant,</para>
<para style="q1">Yahweh, by means of your word.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="66" style="v" />Teach me proper discernment and understanding,</para>
<para style="q1">for I have believed in your commandments.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="67" style="v" />Before I was afflicted I went astray,</para>
<para style="q1">but now I observe your word.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="68" style="v" />You are good, and you are one who does good;</para>
<para style="q1">teach me your statutes.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="69" style="v" />The arrogant have smeared me with lies,</para>
<para style="q1">but I keep your instructions with my whole heart.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="70" style="v" />Their hearts are hardened,</para>
<para style="q1">but I delight in your law.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="71" style="v" />It is good for me that I have suffered</para>
<para style="q1">so that I would learn your statutes.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="72" style="v" />Instruction from your mouth is more precious to me</para>
<para style="q1">than thousands of pieces of gold and silver.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>YOD
<para style="q1">
<verse number="73" style="v" />Your hands have made and fashioned me;</para>
<para style="q1">give me understanding so that I may learn your commandments.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="74" style="v" />Those who honor you will be glad when they see me</para>
<para style="q1">because I find hope in your word.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="75" style="v" />I know, Yahweh, that your decrees are just,</para>
<para style="q1">and that in faithfulness you afflicted me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="76" style="v" />Let your covenant faithfulness comfort me,</para>
<para style="q1">as you promised your servant.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="77" style="v" />Show me compassion so that I may live,</para>
<para style="q1">for your law is my delight.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="78" style="v" />Let the proud be put to shame,</para>
<para style="q1">for they have slandered me;</para>
<para style="q1">but I will meditate on your instructions.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="79" style="v" />May those who honor you turn to me,</para>
<para style="q1">those who know your covenant decrees.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="80" style="v" />May my heart be blameless with respect to your statutes</para>
<para style="q1">so that I may not be put to shame.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>KAPH
<para style="q1">
<verse number="81" style="v" />I faint with longing that you might rescue me!</para>
<para style="q1">I hope in your word.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="82" style="v" />My eyes long to see your promise;</para>
<para style="q1">when will you comfort me?
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="83" style="v" />For I have become like a wineskin in the smoke;</para>
<para style="q1">I do not forget your statutes.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="84" style="v" />How long must your servant endure this;</para>
<para style="q1">when will you judge those who persecute me?
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="85" style="v" />The proud have dug pits for me,</para>
<para style="q1">defying your law.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="86" style="v" />All your commandments are reliable;</para>
<para style="q1">those people persecute me wrongfully; help me.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="87" style="v" />They have almost made an end to me on earth,</para>
<para style="q1">but I do not reject your instructions.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="88" style="v" />By your steadfast love, keep me alive,</para>
<para style="q1">so that I may obey your commands.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>LAMEDH
<para style="q1">
<verse number="89" style="v" />Yahweh, your word stands forever;</para>
<para style="q1">your word is established firmly in heaven.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="90" style="v" />Your faithfulness lasts for all generations;</para>
<para style="q1">you have established the earth, and it remains.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="91" style="v" />All things continue to this day, just as you said in your righteous decrees,</para>
<para style="q1">for all things are your servants.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="92" style="v" />If your law had not been my delight,</para>
<para style="q1">I would have perished in my affliction.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="93" style="v" />I will never forget your instructions,</para>
<para style="q1">for through them you have kept me alive.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="94" style="v" />I am yours; save me,</para>
<para style="q1">for I seek your instructions.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="95" style="v" />The wicked prepare to destroy me,</para>
<para style="q1">but I will seek to understand your covenant decrees.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="96" style="v" />I have seen that everything has its limits,</para>
<para style="q1">but your commandments are broad, beyond limits.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>MEM
<para style="q1">
<verse number="97" style="v" />Oh how I love your law!</para>
<para style="q1">It is my meditation all day long.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="98" style="v" />Your commandments make me wiser than my enemies,</para>
<para style="q1">for your commandments are always with me.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="99" style="v" />I have more understanding than all my teachers,</para>
<para style="q1">for I meditate on your covenant decrees.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="100" style="v" />I understand more than those older than I am;</para>
<para style="q1">this is because I have kept your instructions.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="101" style="v" />I have kept my feet back from every evil path</para>
<para style="q1">so that I might observe your word.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="102" style="v" />I have not turned aside from your righteous decrees,</para>
<para style="q1">for you have instructed me.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="103" style="v" />How sweet are your words to my taste,</para>
<para style="q1">yes, sweeter than honey to my mouth!</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="104" style="v" />Through your instructions I gain discernment;</para>
<para style="q1">therefore I hate every false way.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>NUN
<para style="q1">
<verse number="105" style="v" />Your word is a lamp to my feet</para>
<para style="q1">and a light for my path.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="106" style="v" />I have sworn and have confirmed it,</para>
<para style="q1">that I will observe your righteous decrees.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="107" style="v" />I am very afflicted;</para>
<para style="q1">keep me alive, Yahweh, as you have promised in your word.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="108" style="v" />Yahweh, please accept the freewill offerings of my mouth,</para>
<para style="q1">and teach me your righteous decrees.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="109" style="v" />My life is always in my hand,</para>
<para style="q1">yet I do not forget your law.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="110" style="v" />The wicked have set a snare for me,</para>
<para style="q1">but I have not strayed from your instructions.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="111" style="v" />I claim your covenant decrees as my heritage forever,</para>
<para style="q1">for they are the joy of my heart.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="112" style="v" />My heart is set on obeying your statutes</para>
<para style="q1">forever to the very end.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>SAMEKH
<para style="q1">
<verse number="113" style="v" />I hate those who have a double mind,</para>
<para style="q1">but I love your law.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="114" style="v" />You are my hiding place and my shield;</para>
<para style="q1">I hope in your word.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="115" style="v" />Get away from me, you evil doers,</para>
<para style="q1">so that I may observe the commandments of my God.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="116" style="v" />Sustain me by your word so that I may live</para>
<para style="q1">and not be ashamed of my hope.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="117" style="v" />Support me, and I will be safe;</para>
<para style="q1">I will always meditate on your statutes.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="118" style="v" />You reject all those who stray from your statutes,</para>
<para style="q1">for those people are deceptive and unreliable.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="119" style="v" />You remove all the wicked of the earth like slag;</para>
<para style="q1">therefore I love your solemn commands.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="120" style="v" />My body trembles in fear of you,</para>
<para style="q1">and I am afraid of your righteous decrees.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>AYIN
<para style="q1">
<verse number="121" style="v" />I do what is just and right;</para>
<para style="q1">do not abandon me to my oppressors.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="122" style="v" />Guarantee the welfare of your servant;</para>
<para style="q1">do not let the proud oppress me.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="123" style="v" />My eyes grow tired as I wait for your salvation</para>
<para style="q1">and for your righteous word.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="124" style="v" />Show your servant your covenant faithfulness,</para>
<para style="q1">and teach me your statutes.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="125" style="v" />I am your servant; give me understanding</para>
<para style="q1">so that I may know your covenant decrees.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="126" style="v" />It is time for Yahweh to act,</para>
<para style="q1">for people have broken your law.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="127" style="v" />Truly I love your commandments</para>
<para style="q1">more than gold, more than fine gold.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="128" style="v" />Therefore I carefully follow all your instructions,</para>
<para style="q1">and I hate every path of falsehood.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>PE
<para style="q1">
<verse number="129" style="v" />Your rules are wonderful,</para>
<para style="q1">that is why I obey them.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="130" style="v" />The unfolding of your words gives light;</para>
<para style="q1">it gives understanding to the untrained.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="131" style="v" />I open my mouth and pant,</para>
<para style="q1">for I long for your commandments.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="132" style="v" />Turn to me and have mercy on me,</para>
<para style="q1">as you always do for those who love your name.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="133" style="v" />Direct my footsteps by your word;</para>
<para style="q1">do not let any sin rule me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="134" style="v" />Redeem me from human oppression</para>
<para style="q1">so that I may observe your instructions.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="135" style="v" />Let your face shine on your servant,</para>
<para style="q1">and teach me your statutes.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="136" style="v" />Streams of tears run down from my eyes</para>
<para style="q1">because people do not observe your law.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>TSADHE
<para style="q1">
<verse number="137" style="v" />You are righteous, Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">and your decrees are fair.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="138" style="v" />You have given your covenant decrees righteously</para>
<para style="q1">and faithfully.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="139" style="v" />Anger has destroyed me</para>
<para style="q1">because my adversaries forget your words.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="140" style="v" />Your word has been tested very much,</para>
<para style="q1">and your servant loves it.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="141" style="v" />I am insignificant and despised,</para>
<para style="q1">yet I do not forget your instructions.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="142" style="v" />Your justice is forever right,</para>
<para style="q1">and your law is trustworthy.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="143" style="v" />Though distress and anguish have found me,</para>
<para style="q1">your commandments are still my delight.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="144" style="v" />Your covenant decrees are righteous forever;</para>
<para style="q1">give me understanding that I may live.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>QOPH
<para style="q1">
<verse number="145" style="v" />I cried out with my whole heart, "Answer me, Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">I will keep your statutes.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="146" style="v" />I call to you; save me,</para>
<para style="q1">and I will observe your covenant decrees."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="147" style="v" />I rise before the dawn of the morning and cry for help.</para>
<para style="q1">I hope in your words.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="148" style="v" />My eyes are open before the night watches change</para>
<para style="q1">so that I might meditate on your word.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="149" style="v" />Hear my voice in your covenant faithfulness;</para>
<para style="q1">keep me alive, Yahweh, as you have promised in your righteous decrees.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="150" style="v" />Those who are persecuting me are coming closer to me,</para>
<para style="q1">but they are far from your law.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="151" style="v" />You are near, Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">and all your commandments are trustworthy.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="152" style="v" />Long ago I learned from your covenant decrees</para>
<para style="q1">that you had set them in place forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>RESH
<para style="q1">
<verse number="153" style="v" />Look on my affliction and help me,</para>
<para style="q1">for I do not forget your law.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="154" style="v" />Plead my cause and redeem me;</para>
<para style="q1">keep me, as you have promised in your word.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="155" style="v" />Salvation is far from the wicked,</para>
<para style="q1">for they do not love your statutes.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="156" style="v" />Great are your merciful actions, Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">keep me alive, as you always do.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="157" style="v" />My persecutors and my foes are many,</para>
<para style="q1">yet I have not turned from your covenant decrees.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="158" style="v" />I view the treacherous with disgust</para>
<para style="q1">because they do not keep your word.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="159" style="v" />See how I love your instructions;</para>
<para style="q1">keep me alive, Yahweh, as you have promised by your covenant faithfulness.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="160" style="v" />The essence of your word is truth;</para>
<para style="q1">every one of your righteous decrees lasts forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>SHIN
<para style="q1">
<verse number="161" style="v" />Princes persecute me without cause,</para>
<para style="q1">but my heart stands in awe of your word.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="162" style="v" />I rejoice at your word</para>
<para style="q1">like one who finds great plunder.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="163" style="v" />I hate and despise falsehood,</para>
<para style="q1">but I love your law.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="164" style="v" />Seven times a day I praise you</para>
<para style="q1">because of your righteous decrees.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="165" style="v" />Great peace they have, those who love your law;</para>
<para style="q1">nothing makes them stumble.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="166" style="v" />I hope for your salvation, Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">and I obey your commandments.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="167" style="v" />I observe your solemn commands,</para>
<para style="q1">and I love them greatly.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="168" style="v" />I keep your instructions and your solemn commands,</para>
<para style="q1">for you are aware of everything I do.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="qa"></para>TAV
<para style="q1">
<verse number="169" style="v" />Listen to my cry for help, Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">give me understanding into your word.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="170" style="v" />May my plea come before you;</para>
<para style="q1">help me, as you have promised in your word.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="171" style="v" />May my lips pour out praise,</para>
<para style="q1">for you teach me your statutes.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="172" style="v" />Let my tongue sing about your word,</para>
<para style="q1">for all your commandments are right.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="173" style="v" />May your hand help me,</para>
<para style="q1">for I have chosen your instructions.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="174" style="v" />I long for your rescue, Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">and your law is my delight.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="175" style="v" />May I live and praise you,</para>
<para style="q1">and may your righteous decrees help me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="176" style="v" />I have wandered off like a lost sheep;</para>
<para style="q1">seek your servant,</para>
<para style="q1">for I have not forgotten your commandments.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="120" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song of ascents.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />In my distress I called out to Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">and he answered me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Rescue my life, Yahweh, from those who lie with their lips</para>
<para style="q1">and deceive with their tongues.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />How will he punish you, and what more will he do to you,</para>
<para style="q1">you who have a lying tongue?</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />He will punish you with the arrows of a warrior</para>
<para style="q1">sharpened over burning coals of the broom tree.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Woe is me because I temporarily live in Meshech;</para>
<para style="q1">I lived previously among the tents of Kedar.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />For too long I have lived</para>
<para style="q1">with those who hate peace.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />I am for peace,</para>
<para style="q1">but when I speak, they are for war.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="121" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song of ascents.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />I will lift up my eyes to the mountains.</para>
<para style="q1">From where will my help come?</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />My help comes from Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">who made heaven and earth.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />He will not allow your foot to slip;</para>
<para style="q1">he who protects you will not slumber.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />See, the guardian of Israel</para>
<para style="q1">never slumbers or sleeps.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Yahweh is your guardian;</para>
<para style="q1">Yahweh is the shade at your right hand.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />The sun will not harm you by day,</para>
<para style="q1">nor the moon by night.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Yahweh will protect you from all harm,</para>
<para style="q1">and he will protect your life.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Yahweh will protect you in all you do</para>
<para style="q1">now and forevermore.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="122" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song of ascents, of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />I was glad when they said to me,</para>
<para style="q1">"Let us go to the house of Yahweh."</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Jerusalem, our feet are standing</para>
<para style="q1">within your gates!</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Jerusalem, built</para>
<para style="q1">as a city carefully planned!
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />The tribes go up to Jerusalem—the tribes of Yahweh—</para>
<para style="q1">as a testimony for Israel,</para>
<para style="q1">to give thanks to the name of Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />There thrones of judgment were set,</para>
<para style="q1">thrones of the house of David.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Pray for the peace of Jerusalem!</para>
<para style="q1">"May those who love you have peace.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />May there be peace within the walls that defend you,</para>
<para style="q1">and may they have peace within your fortresses."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />For the sake of my brothers and my friends</para>
<para style="q1">I will say, "May there be peace within you."</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />For the sake of the house of Yahweh our God,</para>
<para style="q1">I will seek good for you.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="123" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song of ascents.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />To you I lift up my eyes,</para>
<para style="q1">you who are enthroned in the heavens.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />See, as the eyes of servants look to their master's hand,</para>
<para style="q1">as the eyes of a maid look to her mistress's hand,</para>
<para style="q1">so our eyes look to Yahweh our God</para>
<para style="q1">until he has mercy on us.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Have mercy on us, Yahweh, have mercy on us,</para>
<para style="q1">for we are filled with humiliation.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />We are more than full</para>
<para style="q1">of the scoffing of the insolent</para>
<para style="q1">and with the contempt of the proud.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="124" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song of ascents; of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />"If Yahweh had not been on our side,"</para>
<para style="q1">let Israel say now,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />"if it had not been Yahweh who was on our side</para>
<para style="q1">when men rose up against us,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />then they would have swallowed us up alive</para>
<para style="q1">when their anger raged against us.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />The water would have swept us away;</para>
<para style="q1">the torrent would have overwhelmed us.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Then the raging waters would have drowned us."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Blessed be Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">who has not allowed us to be torn by their teeth.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />We have escaped like a bird out of the snare of the fowlers;</para>
<para style="q1">the snare has been broken, and we have escaped.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Our help is in Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">who made heaven and earth.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="125" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song of ascents.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Those who trust in Yahweh</para>
<para style="q1">are like Mount Zion, unshakable, forever enduring.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />As the mountains surround Jerusalem,</para>
<para style="q1">so Yahweh surrounds his people</para>
<para style="q1">now and forever.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />The scepter of wickedness must not rule in the land of the righteous.</para>
<para style="q1">Otherwise the righteous might do what is wrong.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Do good, Yahweh, to those who are good</para>
<para style="q1">and to those who are upright in their hearts.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />But as for those who turn aside to their crooked ways,</para>
<para style="q1">Yahweh will lead them away with the evildoers.</para>
<para style="q1">May peace be on Israel.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="126" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song of ascents.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />When Yahweh restored the fortunes of Zion,</para>
<para style="q1">we were like those who dream.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Then our mouths were filled with laughter</para>
<para style="q1">and our tongues with singing.</para>
<para style="q1">Then they said among the nations,</para>
<para style="q1">"Yahweh has done great things for them."</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Yahweh did great things for us;</para>
<para style="q1">how glad we were!
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Restore our fortunes, Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">like the streams in the Negev.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Those who sow in tears will reap with shouts of joy.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />He who goes out weeping, carrying seed for sowing,</para>
<para style="q1">will return again with shouts of joy, bringing his bundles of grain with him.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="127" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song of ascents, of Solomon.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Unless Yahweh builds the house,</para>
<para style="q1">they work uselessly, those who build it.</para>
<para style="q1">Unless Yahweh guards the city,</para>
<para style="q1">the watchman stands guard uselessly.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />It is useless for you to rise up early,</para>
<para style="q1">to come home late,</para>
<para style="q1">or to eat the bread of hard work,</para>
<para style="q1">for Yahweh provides for his beloved as they sleep.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />See, children are a heritage from Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">and the fruit of the womb is a reward from him.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Like arrows in the hand of a warrior,</para>
<para style="q1">so are the children of one's youth.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />How blessed is the man that has his quiver full of them.</para>
<para style="q1">He will not be put to shame</para>
<para style="q1">when he confronts his enemies in the gate.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="128" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song of ascents.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Blessed is everyone who honors Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">who walks in his ways.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />What your hands provide, you will enjoy;</para>
<para style="q1">you will be blessed and prosper.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Your wife will be like a fruitful vine</para>
<para style="q1">in your house;</para>
<para style="q1">your children will be like olive plants</para>
<para style="q1">as they sit around your table.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Yes, indeed, the man will be blessed</para>
<para style="q1">who honors Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />May Yahweh bless you from Zion;</para>
<para style="q1">may you see the prosperity of Jerusalem all the days of your life.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />May you live to see your children's children.</para>
<para style="q1">May peace be on Israel.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="129" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song of ascents.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />"Often since my youth they have attacked me,"</para>
<para style="q1">let Israel say.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />"Often since my youth they have attacked me,</para>
<para style="q1">yet they have not defeated me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />The plowers plowed on my back;</para>
<para style="q1">they made their furrows long.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Yahweh is righteous;</para>
<para style="q1">he has cut the ropes of the wicked."</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />May they all be put to shame and turned back,</para>
<para style="q1">those who hate Zion.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />May they be like the grass on the housetops</para>
<para style="q1">that withers before it grows up,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />that cannot fill the reaper's hand</para>
<para style="q1">or the chest of the one who binds bundles of grain together.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />May those who pass by not say,</para>
<para style="q1">"May the blessing of Yahweh be on you;</para>
<para style="q1">we bless you in the name of Yahweh."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="130" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song of ascents.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Out of the depths I cry to you, Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Lord, hear my voice;</para>
<para style="q1">let your ears be attentive</para>
<para style="q1">to my pleas for mercy.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />If you, Yahweh, would mark iniquities,</para>
<para style="q1">Lord, who could stand?</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />But there is forgiveness with you,</para>
<para style="q1">that you may be revered.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />I wait for Yahweh, my soul waits,</para>
<para style="q1">and in his word I hope.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />My soul waits for the Lord</para>
<para style="q1">more than watchmen wait for the morning.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Israel, hope in Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">Yahweh is merciful,</para>
<para style="q1">and he is very willing to forgive.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />It is he who will redeem Israel</para>
<para style="q1">from all his sins.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="131" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song of ascents; of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Yahweh, my heart is not proud or my eyes haughty.</para>
<para style="q1">I do not have great hopes for myself</para>
<para style="q1">or concern myself with things that are beyond me.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Indeed I have stilled and quieted my soul;</para>
<para style="q1">like a weaned child with his mother,</para>
<para style="q1">my soul within me is like a weaned child.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Israel, hope in Yahweh</para>
<para style="q1">now and forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="132" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song of ascents.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Yahweh, for David's sake call to mind</para>
<para style="q1">all his afflictions.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Call to mind how he swore to Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">how he vowed to the Mighty One of Jacob.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />He said, "I will not enter my house</para>
<para style="q1">or get into my bed,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />I will not give sleep to my eyes</para>
<para style="q1">or rest to my eyelids</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />until I find a place for Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">a tabernacle for the Mighty One of Jacob."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />See, we heard about it in Ephrathah;</para>
<para style="q1">we found it in the fields of Jaar.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />We will go into God's tabernacle;</para>
<para style="q1">we will worship at his footstool.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Arise, Yahweh, to your resting place,</para>
<para style="q1">you and the ark of your strength!
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />May your priests be clothed with integrity;</para>
<para style="q1">may your faithful ones shout for joy.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />For your servant David's sake,</para>
<para style="q1">do not turn away from your anointed king.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />Yahweh swore a sure oath to David,</para>
<para style="q1">a sure oath that he will not revoke:</para>
<para style="q1">"I will place one of your descendants on your throne.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />If your sons keep my covenant</para>
<para style="q1">and the laws that I will teach them,</para>
<para style="q1">their children also will sit on your throne forevermore."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />Certainly Yahweh has chosen Zion,</para>
<para style="q1">he has desired her for his seat.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />"This is my resting place forever.</para>
<para style="q1">I will live here, for I desire her.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />I will abundantly bless her with provisions.</para>
<para style="q1">I will satisfy her poor with bread.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />I will clothe her priests with salvation,</para>
<para style="q1">her faithful ones will shout aloud for joy.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />There I will make a horn to sprout for David</para>
<para style="q1">and set up a lamp for my anointed one.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />I will clothe his enemies with shame,</para>
<para style="q1">but on him his crown will shine."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="133" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song of ascents, of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Behold, how good and how pleasant it is</para>
<para style="q1">for brothers to live together!
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />It is like fine oil on the head</para>
<para style="q1">pouring down on the beard—</para>
<para style="q1">Aaron's beard,</para>
<para style="q1">and then it pours down on the collar of his robes.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />It is like the dew of Hermon</para>
<para style="q1">which falls on the mountains of Zion.</para>
<para style="q1">For there Yahweh commanded the blessing—</para>
<para style="q1">life forevermore.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="134" style="c" />
<para style="d">A song of ascents.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Come, bless Yahweh, all you servants of Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">you who serve during the night in Yahweh's house.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Lift up your hands to the holy place</para>
<para style="q1">and bless Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />May Yahweh bless you from Zion,</para>
<para style="q1">he who made heaven and earth.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="135" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Praise Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise the name of Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise him, you servants of Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />you who stand in Yahweh's house,</para>
<para style="q1">in the courtyards of the house of our God.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Praise Yahweh, for he is good;</para>
<para style="q1">sing praises to his name, for it is pleasant to do so.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />For Yahweh has chosen Jacob for himself,</para>
<para style="q1">Israel as his possession.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />I know that Yahweh is great,</para>
<para style="q1">that our Lord is above all gods.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Whatever Yahweh desires, he does</para>
<para style="q1">in heaven, on earth, in the seas and all the ocean depths.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />He brings the clouds from far away,</para>
<para style="q1">making lightning bolts accompany the rain</para>
<para style="q1">and bringing the wind out of his storehouse.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />He killed the firstborn of Egypt,</para>
<para style="q1">both of man and animals.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />He sent signs and wonders into your midst, Egypt,</para>
<para style="q1">against Pharaoh and all his servants.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />He attacked many nations</para>
<para style="q1">and killed mighty kings,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />Sihon king of the Amorites</para>
<para style="q1">and Og king of Bashan</para>
<para style="q1">and all the kingdoms of Canaan.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />He gave us their land as an inheritance,</para>
<para style="q1">an inheritance to Israel his people.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />Your name, Yahweh, endures forever;</para>
<para style="q1">your renown, Yahweh, endures throughout all generations.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />For Yahweh defends his people</para>
<para style="q1">and has compassion on his servants.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />The nations' idols are silver and gold,</para>
<para style="q1">the work of men's hands.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />Those idols have mouths, but they do not speak;</para>
<para style="q1">they have eyes, but they do not see;</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />they have ears, but they do not hear,</para>
<para style="q1">nor is there breath in their mouths.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />Those who make them are like them,</para>
<para style="q1">as is everyone who trusts in them.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="19" style="v" />Descendants of Israel, bless Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">descendants of Aaron, bless Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="20" style="v" />Descendants of Levi, bless Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">you who honor Yahweh, bless Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="21" style="v" />Blessed be Yahweh in Zion,</para>
<para style="q1">he who lives in Jerusalem.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="136" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Oh, give thanks to Yahweh; for he is good,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Oh, give thanks to the God of gods,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Oh, give thanks to the Lord of lords,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Give thanks to him who alone does great wonders,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />to him who by wisdom made the heavens,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Give thanks to him who spread out the earth above the waters,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />to him who made great lights,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Give thank to him who gave the sun to rule by day,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />the moon and stars to rule by night,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />Give thanks to him who killed the firstborn of Egypt,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />and brought out Israel from among them,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />with a strong hand and a raised arm,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />Give thanks to him who divided the Sea of Reeds,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />and made Israel to pass through the middle of it,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />but overthrew Pharaoh and his army in the Sea of Reeds,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />Give thanks to him who led his people through the wilderness,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />to him who killed great kings,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />Give thanks to him who killed famous kings,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="19" style="v" />Sihon king of the Amorites,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="20" style="v" />and Og king of Bashan,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="21" style="v" />Give thanks to him who gave their land as an inheritance,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="22" style="v" />an inheritance to Israel his servant,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="23" style="v" />to him who called us to mind and helped us in our humiliation,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="24" style="v" />Give thanks to him who has given us victory over our enemies,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="25" style="v" />who gives food to all living beings,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="26" style="v" />Oh, give thanks to the God of heaven,</para>
<para style="q1">for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="137" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />By the rivers of Babylon</para>
<para style="q1">we sat down and wept</para>
<para style="q1">when we thought about Zion.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />On the poplars there</para>
<para style="q1">we hung our harps.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />There our captors required songs from us,</para>
<para style="q1">and those who mocked us required us to be happy, saying,</para>
<para style="q1">"Sing us one of the songs of Zion."</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />How could we sing a song about Yahweh</para>
<para style="q1">in a foreign land?
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />If I ignore the memory of you, Jerusalem,</para>
<para style="q1">let my right hand forget her skill.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Let my tongue cling to the roof of my mouth</para>
<para style="q1">if I think about you no more,</para>
<para style="q1">if I do not prefer Jerusalem</para>
<para style="q1">more than my greatest delights.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Call to mind, Yahweh, what the Edomites did</para>
<para style="q1">on the day Jerusalem fell.</para>
<para style="q1">They said, "Tear it down, tear it down</para>
<para style="q1">to its foundations."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Daughter of Babylon, soon to be destroyed—</para>
<para style="q1">may the person be blessed, whoever pays you back</para>
<para style="q1">for what you have done to us.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />May the person be blessed, whoever takes and dashes your little ones</para>
<para style="q1">against a rock.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="138" style="c" />
<para style="d">A psalm of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />I will give you thanks with my whole heart;</para>
<para style="q1">before the gods I will sing praises to you.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />I will bow down toward your holy temple</para>
<para style="q1">and give thanks to your name for your covenant faithfulness and for your trustworthiness.</para>
<para style="q1">You have made your word and your name more important than anything else.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />On the day that I called you, you answered me;</para>
<para style="q1">you made me bold and strengthened my soul.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />All the kings of the earth will give you thanks, Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">for they will hear the words from your mouth.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Indeed, they will sing of the deeds of Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">for great is the glory of Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />For though Yahweh is high, yet he cares for the lowly,</para>
<para style="q1">but the proud he knows from far off.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Though I walk in the middle of danger, you will preserve my life;</para>
<para style="q1">you will reach out with your hand against the anger of my enemies,</para>
<para style="q1">and your right hand will save me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Yahweh is with me to the end;</para>
<para style="q1">your covenant faithfulness, Yahweh, endures forever.</para>
<para style="q1">Do not forsake the ones whom your hands have made.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="139" style="c" />
<para style="d">For the chief musician. A psalm of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Yahweh, you have examined me, and you know me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />You know when I sit down and when I get up;</para>
<para style="q1">you understand my thoughts from far away.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />You observe my path and my lying down;</para>
<para style="q1">you are familiar with all my ways.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />For before there is a word on my tongue,</para>
<para style="q1">you know it completely, Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Behind me and before me you surround me</para>
<para style="q1">and place your hand upon me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Such knowledge is too much for me;</para>
<para style="q1">it is too high, and I cannot reach it.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Where can I go from your Spirit?</para>
<para style="q1">Where can I flee from your presence?</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />If I ascend up to the heavens, you are there;</para>
<para style="q1">if I make my bed in Sheol, behold, you are there.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />If I fly away on the wings of the morning</para>
<para style="q1">and go to live in the uttermost parts across the sea,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />even there your hand will lead me,</para>
<para style="q1">your right hand will hold on to me.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />If I said, "Surely the darkness will cover me,</para>
<para style="q1">and the light will become night around me,"</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />even the darkness would not be dark to you.</para>
<para style="q1">The night would shine like the day,</para>
<para style="q1">for the darkness and the light are both alike to you.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />You formed my inner parts;</para>
<para style="q1">you formed me in my mother's womb.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />I will praise you,</para>
<para style="q1">for I am wonderfully made.</para>
<para style="q1">My soul knows this very well.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />My bones were not hidden from you</para>
<para style="q1">when I was made in private,</para>
<para style="q1">when I was intricately made in the depths of the earth.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />You saw me inside the womb;</para>
<para style="q1">all the days assigned to me were recorded</para>
<para style="q1">in your book even before the first one happened.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />How precious are your thoughts to me, God!</para>
<para style="q1">How vast is their sum!</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />If I tried to count them, they would be more in number than the sand.</para>
<para style="q1">When I awake, I am still with you.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="19" style="v" />If only you would kill the wicked, God;</para>
<para style="q1">get away from me, you violent men.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="20" style="v" />They rebel against you and act deceitfully;</para>
<para style="q1">your enemies tell lies.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="21" style="v" />Do I not hate those, Yahweh, who hate you?</para>
<para style="q1">Do I not despise those who rise up against you?</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="22" style="v" />I hate them completely;</para>
<para style="q1">they have become my enemies.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="23" style="v" />Examine me, God, and know my heart;</para>
<para style="q1">test me and know my thoughts.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="24" style="v" />See if there is any wicked way in me,</para>
<para style="q1">and lead me in the everlasting way.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="140" style="c" />
<para style="d">For the chief musician. A psalm of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Yahweh, rescue me from the wicked;</para>
<para style="q1">preserve me from violent men.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />They plan evil in their hearts;</para>
<para style="q1">they cause battles every day.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Their tongues wound like serpents;</para>
<para style="q1">vipers' poison is on their lips.
<char style="qs">Selah</char>
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Keep me from the hands of the wicked, Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">preserve me from violent men</para>
<para style="q1">who plan to knock me over.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />The proud have set a trap for me;</para>
<para style="q1">they have spread a net;</para>
<para style="q1">they have set a snare for me.
<char style="qs">Selah</char>
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />I said to Yahweh, "You are my God;</para>
<para style="q1">listen to my cries for mercy."</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Yahweh, my Lord, you are powerfully able to save me;</para>
<para style="q1">you shield my head in the day of battle.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Yahweh, do not grant the desires of the wicked;</para>
<para style="q1">do not let their plots succeed.
<char style="qs">Selah</char>
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />Those who surround me raise their heads;</para>
<para style="q1">let the mischief of their own lips cover them.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />Let burning coals fall on them;</para>
<para style="q1">throw them into the fire,</para>
<para style="q1">into bottomless pits, never more to rise.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />May men of tongues not be made secure on the earth;</para>
<para style="q1">may evil hunt down the violent man to strike him dead.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />I know that Yahweh will judge in favor of the afflicted,</para>
<para style="q1">and that he will give justice to the needy.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />Surely the righteous people will give thanks to your name;</para>
<para style="q1">the upright people will live in your presence.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="141" style="c" />
<para style="d">A psalm of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Yahweh, I am crying out to you; come quickly to me.</para>
<para style="q1">Listen to me when I call to you.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />May my prayer be like incense before you;</para>
<para style="q1">may my lifted hands be like the evening sacrifice.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Yahweh, place a guard over my mouth;</para>
<para style="q1">guard the door of my lips.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Do not let my heart desire any evil thing</para>
<para style="q1">or participate in sinful activities</para>
<para style="q1">with men who behave wickedly.</para>
<para style="q1">May I not eat any of their delicacies.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Let a righteous man hit me; it will be a kindness to me.</para>
<para style="q1">Let him correct me; it will be like oil on my head;</para>
<para style="q1">may my head not refuse to accept it.</para>
<para style="q1">But my prayer is always against their wicked deeds.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Their leaders will be thrown down from the top of cliffs;</para>
<para style="q1">they will hear that my own words are pleasant.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />They will have to say, "As when one plows and breaks up the ground,</para>
<para style="q1">so our bones have been scattered at the mouth of Sheol."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Surely my eyes are on you, Yahweh, Lord;</para>
<para style="q1">in you I take refuge; do not leave my soul defenseless.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />Protect me from the snares that they have laid for me,</para>
<para style="q1">from the traps of evildoers.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />Let the wicked fall into their own nets</para>
<para style="q1">while I escape.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="142" style="c" />
<para style="d">A maschil of David, when he was in the cave; a prayer.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />With my voice I cry out for help to Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">with my voice I plead for Yahweh's favor.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />I pour out my lament before him;</para>
<para style="q1">I tell him my troubles.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />When my spirit is weak within me,</para>
<para style="q1">you know my path.</para>
<para style="q1">In the way that I walk</para>
<para style="q1">they have hidden a trap for me.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />I look to my right and see</para>
<para style="q1">that there is no one who cares about me.</para>
<para style="q1">There is no escape for me;</para>
<para style="q1">no one cares about my life.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />I called out to you, Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">I said, "You are my refuge,</para>
<para style="q1">my portion in the land of the living.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Listen to my call,</para>
<para style="q1">for I have been brought very low;</para>
<para style="q1">rescue me from my persecutors,</para>
<para style="q1">for they are stronger than I.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Bring my soul out of prison</para>
<para style="q1">so that I may give thanks to your name.</para>
<para style="q1">The righteous will gather around me</para>
<para style="q1">because you have been good to me."
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="143" style="c" />
<para style="d">A psalm of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Hear my prayer, Yahweh; listen to my pleas.</para>
<para style="q1">Because of your faithfulness and righteousness, answer me!</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Do not enter into judgment with your servant,</para>
<para style="q1">for in your sight no one is righteous.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />The enemy has pursued my soul;</para>
<para style="q1">he has crushed me to the ground;</para>
<para style="q1">he has made me to live in darkness</para>
<para style="q1">like those who have been dead a long time.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />My spirit is overwhelmed within me;</para>
<para style="q1">my heart despairs.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />I call to mind the old days;</para>
<para style="q1">I meditate on all your deeds;</para>
<para style="q1">I reflect on your accomplishments.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />I spread my hands out to you;</para>
<para style="q1">my soul thirsts for you in a parched land.
<char style="qs">Selah</char>
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Answer me quickly, Yahweh, because my spirit faints.</para>
<para style="q1">Do not hide your face from me,</para>
<para style="q1">or I will become like those who go down into the pit.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Let me hear your covenant faithfulness in the morning,</para>
<para style="q1">for I trust in you.</para>
<para style="q1">Show me the way where I should walk,</para>
<para style="q1">for I lift up my soul to you.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />Rescue me from my enemies, Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">I flee to you to hide.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />Teach me to do your will,</para>
<para style="q1">for you are my God.</para>
<para style="q1">May your good Spirit</para>
<para style="q1">lead me in the land of uprightness.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />Yahweh, for your name's sake, keep me alive;</para>
<para style="q1">in your righteousness bring my soul out of trouble.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />In your covenant faithfulness cut off my enemies</para>
<para style="q1">and destroy all the enemies of my life,</para>
<para style="q1">for I am your servant.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="144" style="c" />
<para style="d">A psalm of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Blessed be Yahweh, my rock,</para>
<para style="q1">who trains my hands for war</para>
<para style="q1">and my fingers for battle.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />You are my covenant faithfulness and my fortress,</para>
<para style="q1">my high tower and the one who rescues me,</para>
<para style="q1">my shield and the one in whom I take refuge,</para>
<para style="q1">the one who subdues nations under me.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Yahweh, what is man that you take notice of him</para>
<para style="q1">or the son of man that you think about him?</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Man is like a breath;</para>
<para style="q1">his days are like a passing shadow.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Cause the sky to sink and come down, Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">touch the mountains and make them smoke.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Send flashes of lightning and scatter my enemies;</para>
<para style="q1">shoot your arrows and drive them back in confusion.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Reach out your hand from above;</para>
<para style="q1">rescue me out of many waters,</para>
<para style="q1">from the hand of foreigners.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Their mouths speak lies,</para>
<para style="q1">and their right hand is falsehood.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />I will sing a new song to you, God;</para>
<para style="q1">on a lute of ten strings I will sing praises to you,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />who give salvation to kings,</para>
<para style="q1">who rescued David your servant from an evil sword.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />Rescue me and free me from the hand of foreigners.</para>
<para style="q1">Their mouths speak lies,</para>
<para style="q1">and their right hand is falsehood.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />May our sons be like plants who grow to full size in their youth</para>
<para style="q1">and our daughters like carved corner pillars, shapely like those of a palace.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />May our storehouses be full with every kind of produce,</para>
<para style="q1">and may our sheep produce thousands and ten thousands in our fields.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />Then our oxen will have many young.</para>
<para style="q1">No one will break through our walls; there will be no exile</para>
<para style="q1">and no outcry in our streets.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />Blessed is the people with such blessings;</para>
<para style="q1">happy is the people whose God is Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="145" style="c" />
<para style="d">A psalm of praise. Of David.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />I will extol you, my God, King;</para>
<para style="q1">I will bless your name forever and ever.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Every day will I bless you;</para>
<para style="q1">I will praise your name forever and ever.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Great is Yahweh and greatly to be praised;</para>
<para style="q1">his greatness is unsearchable.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />One generation will praise your deeds to the next</para>
<para style="q1">and will proclaim your mighty actions.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />I will meditate on the majesty of your glory</para>
<para style="q1">and on your marvelous deeds.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />They will speak of the power of your awesome works,</para>
<para style="q1">and I will declare your greatness.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />They will declare your abounding goodness,</para>
<para style="q1">and they will sing about your righteousness.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Yahweh is gracious and merciful,</para>
<para style="q1">slow to anger and abounding in covenant faithfulness.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />Yahweh is good to all;</para>
<para style="q1">his tender mercies are over all his works.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />All you have made will give thanks to you, Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">your faithful ones will bless you.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />They will speak of the glory of your kingdom,</para>
<para style="q1">and they will tell of your power.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />They will make known to mankind God's mighty deeds</para>
<para style="q1">and the glorious splendor of his kingdom.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />Your kingdom is an everlasting kingdom,</para>
<para style="q1">and your dominion endures throughout all generations.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />Yahweh supports all who are falling</para>
<para style="q1">and raises up all those who are bent over.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />The eyes of all wait for you;</para>
<para style="q1">you give them their food at the right time.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />You open your hand</para>
<para style="q1">and satisfy the desire of every living thing.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />Yahweh is righteous in all his ways</para>
<para style="q1">and faithful in all he does.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />Yahweh is near to all those who call to him,</para>
<para style="q1">to all who call to him in trustworthiness.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="19" style="v" />He fulfills the desire of those who honor him;</para>
<para style="q1">he hears their cry and saves them.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="20" style="v" />Yahweh watches over all those who love him,</para>
<para style="q1">but he will destroy all the wicked.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="21" style="v" />My mouth will speak out the praise of Yahweh;</para>
<para style="q1">let all mankind bless his holy name forever and ever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="146" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Praise Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise Yahweh, my soul.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />I give praise to Yahweh with all my life;</para>
<para style="q1">I will sing praises to my God as long as I exist.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Do not put your trust in princes</para>
<para style="q1">or in mankind, in whom there is no salvation.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />When a person's life's breath stops, he returns to the ground;</para>
<para style="q1">on that day his plans end.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Blessed is he who has the God of Jacob for his help,</para>
<para style="q1">whose hope is in Yahweh his God.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Yahweh made heaven and earth,</para>
<para style="q1">the sea, and all that is in them;</para>
<para style="q1">he observes trustworthiness forever.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />He executes justice for the oppressed</para>
<para style="q1">and gives food to the hungry.</para>
<para style="q1">Yahweh frees the prisoners;</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />Yahweh opens the eyes of the blind;</para>
<para style="q1">Yahweh raises up those who are bowed down;</para>
<para style="q1">Yahweh loves the righteous people.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />Yahweh protects the foreigners in the land;</para>
<para style="q1">he lifts up the fatherless and widow,</para>
<para style="q1">but he opposes the wicked.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />Yahweh will reign forever,</para>
<para style="q1">your God, Zion, for all generations.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="147" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Praise Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">for it is good to sing praises to our God,</para>
<para style="q1">it is pleasant, and praise is suitable.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Yahweh rebuilds Jerusalem,</para>
<para style="q1">he gathers together the scattered people of Israel.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />He heals the brokenhearted</para>
<para style="q1">and binds up their wounds.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />He counts the stars,</para>
<para style="q1">he gives names to all of them.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Great is our Lord and awesome in power,</para>
<para style="q1">his understanding cannot be measured.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Yahweh lifts up the oppressed,</para>
<para style="q1">he brings the wicked down to the ground.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Sing to Yahweh with thanksgiving,</para>
<para style="q1">sing praises to our God with a harp.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />He covers the heavens with clouds</para>
<para style="q1">and prepares rain for the earth,</para>
<para style="q1">making the grass to grow on the mountains.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />He gives food to the animals</para>
<para style="q1">and to the young ravens when they cry.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />He finds no delight in the strength of a horse,</para>
<para style="q1">he takes no pleasure in the strong legs of a man.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />Yahweh takes pleasure in those who honor him,</para>
<para style="q1">who hope in his covenant faithfulness.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />Praise Yahweh, Jerusalem,</para>
<para style="q1">praise your God, Zion.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />For he strengthens the bars of your gates,</para>
<para style="q1">he blesses your children among you.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />He brings prosperity inside your borders,</para>
<para style="q1">he satisfies you with the finest of wheat.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="15" style="v" />He sends out his commandment to earth,</para>
<para style="q1">his command runs very swiftly.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="16" style="v" />He makes the snow like wool,</para>
<para style="q1">he scatters the frost like ashes.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="17" style="v" />He dispenses the hail like crumbs,</para>
<para style="q1">who can withstand the cold he sends?</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="18" style="v" />He sends out his command and melts them,</para>
<para style="q1">he makes the wind to blow and the water to flow.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="19" style="v" />He proclaimed his word to Jacob,</para>
<para style="q1">his statutes and his righteous decrees to Israel.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="20" style="v" />He has not done so with any other nation,</para>
<para style="q1">and as for his decrees, they do not know them.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="148" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Praise Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise Yahweh, you in the heavens;</para>
<para style="q1">praise him, you in the heights.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Praise him, all his angels;</para>
<para style="q1">praise him, all his hosts.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Praise him, sun and moon;</para>
<para style="q1">praise him, all you shining stars.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Praise him, highest heaven</para>
<para style="q1">and you waters that are above the sky.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Let them praise the name of Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">for he gave the command, and they were created.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />He has also established them forever and ever;</para>
<para style="q1">he issued a decree that will never change.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />Praise him from the earth,</para>
<para style="q1">you sea monsters and all ocean depths,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />fire and hail, snow and clouds,</para>
<para style="q1">stormy wind fulfilling his word.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />Praise him, mountains and all hills,</para>
<para style="q1">fruit trees and all cedars,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="10" style="v" />animals wild and tame,</para>
<para style="q1">creatures that crawl and birds.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="11" style="v" />Praise Yahweh, kings of the earth and all nations,</para>
<para style="q1">princes and all who govern on the earth,</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="12" style="v" />both young men and young women,</para>
<para style="q1">elderly and children.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="13" style="v" />Let them all praise the name of Yahweh,</para>
<para style="q1">for his name alone is exalted</para>
<para style="q1">and his glory extends over the earth and the heavens.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="14" style="v" />He has lifted up the horn of his people</para>
<para style="q1">for praise from all his faithful ones,</para>
<para style="q1">the Israelites, the people near to him.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="149" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Praise Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">Sing to Yahweh a new song;</para>
<para style="q1">sing his praise in the assembly of the faithful ones.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Let Israel rejoice in the one who made them;</para>
<para style="q1">let the people of Zion rejoice in their king.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Let them praise his name with dancing;</para>
<para style="q1">let them sing praises to him with tambourine and harp.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />For Yahweh takes pleasure in his people;</para>
<para style="q1">he glorifies the humble with salvation.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Let the faithful ones rejoice in this honor;</para>
<para style="q1">let them sing for joy on their beds.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />May the praises of God be in their mouths</para>
<para style="q1">and a two-edged sword in their hand</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="7" style="v" />to execute vengeance on the nations</para>
<para style="q1">and acts of punishment on the peoples.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="8" style="v" />They will bind their kings with chains</para>
<para style="q1">and their nobles with iron shackles.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="9" style="v" />They will execute the judgment that is written.</para>
<para style="q1">This will be an honor for all his faithful ones.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise Yahweh.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<chapter number="150" style="c" />
<para style="q1">
<verse number="1" style="v" />Praise Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise God in his holy place;</para>
<para style="q1">praise him in the mighty heavens.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="2" style="v" />Praise him for his mighty acts;</para>
<para style="q1">praise him for his surpassing greatness.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="3" style="v" />Praise him with the blast of the horn;</para>
<para style="q1">praise him with lute and harp.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="4" style="v" />Praise him with tambourines and dancing;</para>
<para style="q1">praise him with stringed instruments and wind instruments.</para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="5" style="v" />Praise him with loud cymbals;</para>
<para style="q1">praise him with high sounding cymbals.
<note caller="u" style="s5"></note></para>
<para style="q1">
<verse number="6" style="v" />Let everything that has breath praise Yahweh.</para>
<para style="q1">Praise Yahweh.</para>